77 ///@TODO: thejaswi: link this option to a theano config variable?
78 static bool g_use_cnmem = false;
79 static const int g_max_devices = 8;
80 int initCnmem(int card_number_provided, int card_nb, size_t mem) {
81     static bool cnmemInitialized = false;
82     if(cnmemInitialized) {
83         return 0;
84     }
85     // On stderr to be at the same place as "Using gpu device..."
86     int numDevices = 0;
87     cnmemDevice_t devices[g_max_devices];
88     if(cudaGetDeviceCount(&numDevices) != cudaSuccess) {
89         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
90                      "initCnmem: 'cudaGetDeviceCount' failed! Reason=%s\n",
91                      cudaGetErrorString(cudaGetLastError()));
92         return -1;
93     }
94     if(card_number_provided){
95         numDevices = 1;
96         int i = 0;
97         devices[i].device = card_nb;
98         devices[i].size = mem;
99         ///@TODO: thejaswi: add support for multiple streams
100         devices[i].numStreams = 0;
101         devices[i].streams = NULL;
102         devices[i].streamSizes = NULL;
103     }else{
104         for(int i=0;i<numDevices;++i) {
105             devices[i].device = i;
106             devices[i].size = mem;
107             ///@TODO: thejaswi: add support for multiple streams
108             devices[i].numStreams = 0;
109             devices[i].streams = NULL;
110         }
111     }
112 
113     ///@TODO: thejaswi: passing custom cnmem flags?
114     cnmemStatus_t status = cnmemInit(numDevices, devices, CNMEM_FLAGS_DEFAULT);
115     if(status != CNMEM_STATUS_SUCCESS) {
116         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
117                      "initCnmem: cnmemInit call failed! Reason=%s. numdev=%d\n",
118                      cnmemGetErrorString(status), numDevices);
119         return -1;
120     }
121     cnmemInitialized = true;
122     return 0;
123 }

125 void * device_malloc(size_t size, int verbose)
126 {
127     #if PRECHECK_ERROR
128         cudaThreadSynchronize();
129         cudaError_t prevError = cudaGetLastError();
130         if (cudaSuccess != prevError)
131         {
132             fprintf(stderr,
133                     "Error existed before calling device_malloc. %s\n",
134                     cudaGetErrorString(prevError)
135                     );
136         }
137     #endif
138     void * rval=NULL;
139     ///@TODO: thejaswi: support for multiple-streams?
140     if(g_use_cnmem) {
141         cnmemStatus_t status = CNMEM_STATUS_SUCCESS;
142         status = cnmemMalloc(&rval, size, NULL);
143         if(status != CNMEM_STATUS_SUCCESS) {
144             PyErr_Format(PyExc_MemoryError,
145                          "Error allocating %zd bytes of device memory (%s).",
146                          size, cnmemGetErrorString(status));
147             return NULL;
148         }
149     }
150     else {
151         cudaError_t err = cudaMalloc(&rval, size);
152         if (cudaSuccess != err)
153         {
154             // Clear the error flag, cudaMalloc doesn't do it.
155             // Currently this returns the same thing as err, but if in future
156             // it returns something else I still don't see why we should ignore
157             // it.  All we want to do here is reset the flag.
158             cudaGetLastError();
159             if (verbose)
160             {
161                 size_t free = 0, total = 0;
162                 cudaError_t err2 = cudaMemGetInfo(&free, &total);
163                 if (err2 != cudaSuccess){
164                     cudaGetLastError();
165                     fprintf(stderr,
166                             "Error when trying to find the memory information"
167                             " on the GPU: %s\n", cudaGetErrorString(err2));
168                 }
169                 #if COMPUTE_GPU_MEM_USED
170                     fprintf(stderr,
171                             "Error allocating %zd bytes of device memory (%s)."
172                             " new total bytes allocated: %d."
173                             " Driver report %zd bytes free and %zd bytes total \n",
174                             size, cudaGetErrorString(err), _allocated_size,
175                             free, total);
176                 #else
177                     fprintf(stderr,
178                             "Error allocating %zd bytes of device memory (%s)."
179                             " Driver report %zd bytes free and %zd bytes total \n",
180                             size, cudaGetErrorString(err), free, total);
181                 #endif
182             }
183             PyErr_Format(PyExc_MemoryError,
184                          "Error allocating %zd bytes of device memory (%s).",
185                          size, cudaGetErrorString(err));
186             return NULL;
187         }
188     }
189     if (rval != NULL){
190         // Can it happen that cudaMalloc return cudaSuccess, but return a NULL ptr?
191         // Could this be what happen if size is 0?
192         _outstanding_mallocs[0] += 1;
193 
194 #if COMPUTE_GPU_MEM_USED
195         _allocated_size += size;
196         _max_allocated_size = std::max(_max_allocated_size, _allocated_size);
197         int i = 0;
198         for(;i<TABLE_SIZE;i++){
199             if(NULL==_alloc_size_table[i].ptr){
200                 _alloc_size_table[i].ptr=rval;
201                 _alloc_size_table[i].size=size;
202                 break;
203             }
204         }
205         if (i == TABLE_SIZE){
206             fprintf(stderr,
207                     "When tracking GPU malloc, our table size wasn't big enough."
208                     " So we loose some tracking. Raise the value of TABLE_SIZE in the file cuda_ndarra.cu");
209         }
210 #endif
211     }
212     //fprintf(stderr,
213     //"allocated %li bytes of device memory (%s). new total bytes allocated: %d. ptr: %p\n",
214     //(long)size, cudaGetErrorString(err),_allocated_size,rval);
215 
216     if(ALLOC_MEMSET){
217         //We init them to nan to make sure we catch more debug case.
218         cudaMemset(rval, 0xFF, size);
219         //printf("MEMSET\n");
220     }
221     #if PRINT_FREE_MALLOC
222         fprintf(stderr, "device malloc %p of size %d\n", rval, size);
223     #endif
224     return rval;
225 }

227 int device_free(void *ptr)
228 {
229     #if PRECHECK_ERROR
230         cudaThreadSynchronize();
231         cudaError_t prevError = cudaGetLastError();
232         if (cudaSuccess != prevError)
233         {
234             fprintf(stderr,
235                     "Error existed before calling device_free. %s\n",
236                     cudaGetErrorString(prevError)
237                     );
238         }
239     #endif
240     #if PRINT_FREE_MALLOC
241         size_t free = 0, total = 0;
242         cudaError_t err2 = cudaMemGetInfo(&free, &total);
243         if (err2 != cudaSuccess){
244             cudaGetLastError();
245             fprintf(stderr,
246                     "Error when tring to find the memory information"
247                     " on the GPU: %s\n", cudaGetErrorString(err2));
248         }
249         #if COMPUTE_GPU_MEM_USED
250         {
251             int i = 0;
252             for(;i<TABLE_SIZE;i++)
253                 if(_alloc_size_table[i].ptr==ptr){
254                     break;
255                 }
256             assert(i<TABLE_SIZE);
257             fprintf(stderr, "device_free %p of size %d."
258                     " Driver report %d bytes free and %d bytes total \n",
259                     ptr, _alloc_size_table[i].size, free, total);
260         }
261         #else
262             fprintf(stderr, "device_free %p."
263                     " Driver report %d bytes free and %d bytes total \n",
264                     ptr, free, total);
265         #endif
266     #endif
267 
268     // if there is no gpu context, the call to cudaFree will fail; skip it entirely
269     if(!g_gpu_context_active) {
270         return 0;
271     }
272 
273     ///@TODO: thejaswi: multi-stream support
274     if(g_use_cnmem) {
275         cnmemStatus_t status = cnmemFree(ptr, NULL);
276         if(status != CNMEM_STATUS_SUCCESS) {
277             fprintf(stderr, "device_free: cnmemFree call failed! Reason=%s\n",
278                     cnmemGetErrorString(status));
279         }
280     }
281     else {
282         // We need sync as the Theano's GC could remove intermediate variable that
283         // are still needed as the gpu kernel are running or in the queue.
284         CNDA_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
285         cudaThreadSynchronize();
286         CNDA_END_ALLOW_THREADS
287 
288         cudaError_t err =  cudaFree(ptr);
289         if (cudaSuccess != err)
290         {
291             // Clear the error flag, cudaFree doesn't do it.
292             // Currently this returns the same thing as err, but if in future
293             // it returns something else I still don't see why we should ignore
294             // it.  All we want to do here is reset the flag.
295             cudaGetLastError();
296             size_t free = 0, total = 0;
297             cudaError_t err2 = cudaMemGetInfo(&free, &total);
298             if (err2 != cudaSuccess){
299                 cudaGetLastError();
300                 fprintf(stderr,
301                         "Error when tring to find the memory information"
302                         " on the GPU: %s\n", cudaGetErrorString(err2));
303             }
304             #if COMPUTE_GPU_MEM_USED
305             {
306                 int i = 0;
307                 for(;i<TABLE_SIZE;i++)
308                     if(_alloc_size_table[i].ptr==ptr){
309                         break;
310                     }
311                 assert(i<TABLE_SIZE);
312                 fprintf(stderr,
313                         "Error freeing device pointer %p (%s) of size %d. %zd byte already allocated."
314                         " Driver report %zd bytes free and %zd bytes total \n",
315                         ptr, cudaGetErrorString(err),
316                         _alloc_size_table[i].size, _allocated_size, free, total);
317             }
318             #else
319                 fprintf(stderr,
320                         "Error freeing device pointer %p (%s)."
321                         " Driver report %zd bytes free and %zd bytes total \n",
322                         ptr,
323                         cudaGetErrorString(err), free, total);
324             #endif
325             if (NULL != PyErr_Occurred()){
326                 fprintf(stderr,
327                         "device_free: cudaFree() returned an error, but there is already an"
328                         " Python error set. This happen during the clean up when there is a"
329                         " first error and the CUDA driver is in a so bad state that it don't"
330                         " work anymore. We keep the previous error set to help debugging it.");
331                 return -1;
332             }
333             PyErr_Format(PyExc_MemoryError,
334                     "error freeing device pointer %p (%s)",
335                     ptr,
336                     cudaGetErrorString(err));
337             return -1;
338         }
339     }
340     _outstanding_mallocs[0] -= (ptr != NULL);
341     #if COMPUTE_GPU_MEM_USED
342         int i=0;
343         size_t total_freed = 0;
344         for(;i<TABLE_SIZE;i++)
345             if(_alloc_size_table[i].ptr==ptr){
346                 _allocated_size -= _alloc_size_table[i].size;
347                 total_freed += _alloc_size_table[i].size;
348                 _alloc_size_table[i].ptr=0;
349                 _alloc_size_table[i].size=0;
350 
351                 break;
352             }
353         //if(i==TABLE_SIZE)
354         //    printf("Unallocated unknow size!\n");
355         //fprintf(stderr, "freed %li bytes of device memory (%s). %d already allocated, ptr=%p\n", (long)total_freed, cudaGetErrorString(err),_allocated_size,ptr);
356     #endif
357     return 0;
358 }

367 static void *work_mem = NULL;
368 static size_t work_size = 0;
369 
370 /*
371  * Returns a chunk of memory for temporary work inside of an op. You can only
372  * request a single chunk of memory at a time since it is reused.
373  */
374 void *get_work_mem(size_t sz) {
375     if (sz <= work_size)
376         return work_mem;
377     device_free(work_mem);
378     work_mem = device_malloc(sz);
379     work_size = sz;
380     if (work_mem == NULL)
381         work_size = 0;
382     return work_mem;
383 }

414 static int
415 CudaNdarray_uninit(CudaNdarray*self)
416 {
417     #if PRINT_FREE_MALLOC
418         fprintf(stderr, "CudaNdarray_uninit %p\n", self);
419     #endif
420     int rval = 0;
421     if (self->data_allocated) {
422         assert(self->devdata);
423         if (device_free(self->devdata))
424         {
425             fprintf(stderr,
426                     "CudaNdarray_uninit: error freeing self->devdata. (self=%p, self->devata=%p)\n",
427                     self, self->devdata);
428             rval = -1;
429         }
430         self->devdata = NULL;
431         self->data_allocated = 0;
432     }
433     if (self->dev_structure)
434     {
435         if (device_free(self->dev_structure))
436         {
437             fprintf(stderr,
438                     "CudaNdarray_uninit: error freeing dev_structure memory %p (self=%p)\n",
439                     self->dev_structure, self);
440             rval = -1;
441         }
442         self->dev_structure = NULL;
443     }
444     if (self->host_structure)
445     {
446         free(self->host_structure);
447         self->host_structure = NULL;
448     }
449     self->nd = -1;
450     Py_XDECREF(self->base);
451     self->base = NULL;
452     return rval;
453 }

456 //make the rightmost coords change fastest
457 //TODO: why does a downward for-loop not work????
458 //TODO: use the log2_dims and driver code to remove / and %
459 //TODO: skip the last division (when d == 0)
460 #define decl_k_elemwise_unary_rowmajor(name, F) \
461 __global__ void name (unsigned int numEls,  \
462         unsigned int nd, \
463         const int * dim,  \
464         const float * a_data, const int * a_str, \
465         float * z_data, const int * z_str) \
466 { \
467     const unsigned int idx = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x; \
468     const unsigned int numThreads = blockDim.x * gridDim.x; \
469  \
470     for (unsigned int i = idx; i < numEls; i += numThreads) \
471     { \
472         unsigned int ii = i; \
473         const float * a_i = a_data; \
474         float * z_i = z_data; \
475         for (unsigned int _d = 0; _d < nd; ++_d) \
476         { \
477             unsigned int d = nd - _d-1;  \
478             int i_d = ii % dim[d]; /* i_d is our position in the d'th dimension   */ \
479             ii = ii / dim[d]; \
480             a_i += i_d * a_str[d]; /* increment our a and z pointers by i_d elements */ \
481             z_i += i_d * z_str[d]; \
482         } \
483         z_i[0] = F(a_i[0]); \
484     } \
485 }

556 PyObject * CudaNdarray_CreateArrayObj(CudaNdarray * self, PyObject *args)
557 {
558     PyObject * dtype = NULL;
559     if (args && !PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "|O", &dtype))
560         return NULL;
561     if (dtype) {
562         PyArray_Descr* dtype2;
563         // PyArray_DescrConverter try to convert anything to a PyArray_Descr.
564         if(!PyArray_DescrConverter(dtype, &dtype2))
565         {
566             PyObject * str = PyObject_Repr(dtype);
567             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
568                          "CudaNdarray dtype parameter not understood: %s",
569                          PyString_AsString(str)
570                          );
571             Py_CLEAR(str);
572             return NULL;
573         }
574         int typeNum = dtype2->type_num;
575         Py_DECREF(dtype2);
576         if (typeNum != NPY_FLOAT32)
577         {
578             PyObject * str = PyObject_Repr(dtype);
579             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
580                          "CudaNdarray support only support float32 dtype, provided: %d",
581                          typeNum
582                          );
583             Py_CLEAR(str);
584             return NULL;
585         }
586     }
587 
588     int verbose = 0;
589     if(self->nd>=0 && CudaNdarray_SIZE(self)==0){
590         npy_intp * npydims = (npy_intp*)malloc(self->nd * sizeof(npy_intp));
591         assert (npydims);
592         for (int i = 0; i < self->nd; ++i) npydims[i] = (npy_intp)(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i]);
593         PyObject * rval = PyArray_SimpleNew(self->nd, npydims, REAL_TYPENUM);
594         free(npydims);
595         if (!rval){
596             return NULL;
597         }
598         assert (PyArray_ITEMSIZE((PyArrayObject *)rval) == sizeof(real));
599         return rval;
600     }
601     if ((self->nd < 0) || (self->devdata == 0))
602     {
603         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "can't copy from un-initialized CudaNdarray");
604         return NULL;
605     }
606     CudaNdarray * contiguous_self = NULL;
607     if (CudaNdarray_is_c_contiguous(self))
608     {
609         contiguous_self = self;
610         Py_INCREF(contiguous_self);
611         if (verbose) std::cerr << "CreateArrayObj already contiguous" << contiguous_self << '\n';
612     }
613     else
614     {
615         contiguous_self = (CudaNdarray*)CudaNdarray_Copy(self);
616         if (verbose) std::cerr << "CreateArrayObj created contiguous" << contiguous_self << '\n';
617     }
618     if (!contiguous_self)
619     {
620         return NULL;
621     }
622 
623     npy_intp * npydims = (npy_intp*)malloc(self->nd * sizeof(npy_intp));
624     assert (npydims);
625     for (int i = 0; i < self->nd; ++i)
626         npydims[i] = (npy_intp)(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i]);
627     PyArrayObject * rval = (PyArrayObject *) PyArray_SimpleNew(self->nd,
628                                                                npydims,
629                                                                REAL_TYPENUM);
630     free(npydims);
631     if (!rval)
632     {
633         Py_DECREF(contiguous_self);
634         return NULL;
635     }
636 
637     assert (PyArray_ITEMSIZE(rval) == sizeof(real));
638 
639     npy_intp rval_size = PyArray_SIZE(rval);
640     void *rval_data = PyArray_DATA(rval);
641     cudaError_t err;
642     CNDA_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS;
643 
644     err = cudaMemcpy(rval_data, contiguous_self->devdata,
645                      rval_size * sizeof(real),
646                      cudaMemcpyDeviceToHost
647                      );
648     //CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;  // unneeded because cudaMemcpy is blocking anyway
649     CNDA_END_ALLOW_THREADS;
650 
651     if (cudaSuccess != err)
652     {
653         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError, "error (%s)copying data to host",
654                      cudaGetErrorString(err));
655         Py_DECREF(rval);
656         rval = NULL;
657     }
658 
659     Py_DECREF(contiguous_self);
660     return (PyObject *)rval;
661 }

663 // TODO-- we have two functions here, ZEROS and Zeros.
664 // ZEROS is meant to be called just from C code (you don't need to pass it PyObject * s)
665 // but this naming is very weird, makes it look like a macro
666 // we should figure out the correct convention and change to that
667 PyObject* CudaNdarray_ZEROS(int n, int * dims)
668 {
669 
670     size_t total_elements = 1;
671 
672     for(size_t i=0;i<n;i++){
673         // Detect overflow on unsigned integer
674         if (dims[i] != 0 && total_elements > (SIZE_MAX / dims[i])) {
675             PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
676                          "Can't store in size_t for the bytes requested %llu * %llu",
677                          (unsigned long long)total_elements,
678                          (unsigned long long)dims[i]);
679             return NULL;
680         }
681         total_elements*=dims[i];
682     }
683 
684     // total_elements now contains the size of the array, in reals
685     if (total_elements > (SIZE_MAX / sizeof(real))){
686         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
687                      "Can't store in size_t for the bytes requested %llu * 4",
688                      (unsigned long long)total_elements);
689         return NULL;
690     }
691     size_t total_size = total_elements * sizeof(real);
692 
693     CudaNdarray* rval = (CudaNdarray*)CudaNdarray_New();
694     if (!rval)
695     {
696         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "CudaNdarray_ZEROS: call to New failed");
697         return NULL;
698     }
699 
700     if (CudaNdarray_alloc_contiguous(rval, n, dims))
701     {
702         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "CudaNdarray_ZEROS: allocation failed.");
703         Py_DECREF(rval);
704         return NULL;
705     }
706 
707     // Fill with zeros
708     //fprintf(stdout, "Sizeof: %d\n", total_size);
709     if (cudaSuccess != cudaMemset(rval->devdata, 0, total_size))
710     {
711         PyErr_Format(PyExc_MemoryError,
712                      "CudaNdarray_ZEROS: Error memsetting %llu bytes of device memory.",
713                      (unsigned long long)total_size);
714         Py_DECREF(rval);
715         return NULL;
716     }
717 
718     if (cnda_copy_structure_to_device(rval))
719     {
720         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "CudaNdarray_ZEROS: syncing structure to device failed");
721         Py_DECREF(rval);
722         return NULL;
723     }
724     return (PyObject*) rval;
725 }

727 // declared as a static method (hence 1st parameter is not used)
728 // Based on _Copy and _dimshuffle
729 PyObject* CudaNdarray_Zeros(PyObject* _unused, PyObject* shape)
730 {
731     if(!shape)
732     {
733         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "CudaNdarray_Zeros: function takes at least 1 argument (0 given)");
734         return NULL;
735     }
736     if(!PySequence_Check(shape))
737     {
738         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "shape argument must be a sequence");
739         return NULL;
740     }
741 
742     int shplen = PySequence_Length(shape);
743 
744     if (shplen == 0)
745     {
746         return CudaNdarray_ZEROS(0, NULL);
747     }
748 
749     int* newdims = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * shplen);
750 
751     if (!newdims)
752     {
753         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_MemoryError,
754             "CudaNdarray_Zeros: Failed to allocate temporary space");
755         return NULL;
756     }
757 
758     // start from the end to compute strides
759     for (int i = shplen-1; i >= 0; --i)
760     {
761         PyObject* shp_el_obj = PySequence_GetItem(shape, i);
762         if(shp_el_obj == NULL)
763         {
764             // shouldn't happen since we checked length before...
765             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "CudaNdarray_Zeros: Index out of bound in sequence");
766             free(newdims);
767             return NULL;
768         }
769 
770         int shp_el = PyInt_AsLong(shp_el_obj);
771         Py_DECREF(shp_el_obj);
772 
773         if (shp_el < 0)
774         {
775             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "CudaNdarray_Zeros: shape must contain only non-negative values for size of a dimension");
776             free(newdims);
777             return NULL;
778         }
779 
780         newdims[i] = shp_el;
781     }
782 
783     PyObject* rval = CudaNdarray_ZEROS(shplen,newdims);
784 
785     free(newdims);
786 
787     return (PyObject*)rval;
788 }

794 PyObject * CudaNdarray_Copy(const CudaNdarray * self)
795 {
796     PyObject * rval = CudaNdarray_New();
797     if ((!rval) || (-1 == self->nd))
798     {
799         return rval;
800     }
801     if (CudaNdarray_alloc_contiguous((CudaNdarray*)rval, self->nd, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)))
802     {
803         Py_DECREF(rval);
804         return NULL;
805     }
806     if (CudaNdarray_CopyFromCudaNdarray((CudaNdarray*)rval, self))
807     {
808         Py_DECREF(rval);
809         return NULL;
810     }
811     return rval;
812 }
813 PyObject * CudaNdarray_DeepCopy(CudaNdarray * self, PyObject * memo)
814 {
815     assert(PyDict_Check(memo));
816     PyObject * selfkey = PyInt_FromLong((long)self);
817     assert(selfkey);
818     if (PyDict_Contains(memo, selfkey))
819     {
820         PyObject * rval = PyDict_GetItem(memo, selfkey);
821         Py_DECREF(selfkey);
822         Py_XINCREF(rval);
823         return rval;
824     }
825     else
826     {
827         PyObject * rval = CudaNdarray_Copy(self);
828         if (0) std::cerr << "DeepCopy created " << rval << " devdata " << ((CudaNdarray*)rval)->devdata << "\n";
829         if (NULL == rval)
830         {
831             Py_DECREF(selfkey);
832             return NULL;
833         }
834         if (PyDict_SetItem(memo, selfkey, rval))
835         {
836             Py_DECREF(rval);
837             Py_DECREF(selfkey);
838             return NULL;
839         }
840         Py_DECREF(selfkey);
841         return rval;
842     }
843 }
844 PyObject * CudaNdarray_ReduceSum(CudaNdarray * self, PyObject * py_reduce_mask)
845 {
846     if (!PySequence_Check(py_reduce_mask))
847     {
848         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "reduce_mask must be sequence of ints");
849         return NULL;
850     }
851     int len = PySequence_Length(py_reduce_mask);
852     if (len != self->nd)
853     {
854         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "length of reduce_mask must match self->nd");
855         return NULL;
856     }
857     CudaNdarray * self_sum = (CudaNdarray*)CudaNdarray_New();
858     if (!self_sum)
859     {
860         return NULL;
861     }
862     //TODO: allocate a fixed size dimshuffle_pattern_cache on the stack,
863     //      and use it if it is big enough.
864     int * dimshuffle_pattern = (int*)malloc(len * 2 * sizeof(int));
865     int * sum_dims = dimshuffle_pattern + len;
866     int n_remaining_dims = 0;
867     if (!dimshuffle_pattern)
868     {
869         Py_DECREF(self_sum);
870         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_MemoryError, "failed to alloc internal storage");
871         return NULL;
872     }
873     for (int i = 0; i < len; ++i)
874     {
875         PyObject *o_i = PySequence_GetItem(py_reduce_mask, i);
876         int o_i_int = PyInt_AsLong(o_i);
877         Py_XDECREF(o_i);
878         if (PyErr_Occurred())
879         {
880             Py_DECREF(self_sum);
881             free(dimshuffle_pattern);
882             return NULL;
883         }
884         if (o_i_int) // this is a dimension over which we are reducing
885         {
886             sum_dims[i] = 1;
887         }
888         else
889         {
890             sum_dims[i] = CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i];
891             dimshuffle_pattern[n_remaining_dims++] = i;
892         }
893     }
894     if (0   || CudaNdarray_alloc_contiguous(self_sum, len, sum_dims)
895             || CudaNdarray_reduce_sum(self_sum, self)
896             || CudaNdarray_dimshuffle(self_sum, n_remaining_dims, dimshuffle_pattern))
897     {
898         Py_DECREF(self_sum);
899         free(dimshuffle_pattern);
900         return NULL;
901     }
902     free(dimshuffle_pattern);
903     return (PyObject*)self_sum;
904 }

906 // Reshape self to the new shape gived by the tuple shape.
907 //
908 // If self is c contiguous, it return a view. Otherwise it always do a copy.
909 // TODO: make it return a view when the strides allow it even if it is not
910 //       c contiguous
911 PyObject * CudaNdarray_Reshape(CudaNdarray * self, PyObject * shape)
912 {
913     if(!CudaNdarray_is_c_contiguous(self))
914     {
915         // allocate new space
916         //TODO: test to see if we can re-use old one and take a new param to
917         //  use this
918         CudaNdarray* rval = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_Copy(self);
919         if (!rval)
920         {
921             return NULL;
922         }
923 
924         CudaNdarray* ret = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_Reshape(rval, shape);
925         Py_XDECREF(rval);
926         return (PyObject*)ret;
927     }
928 
929     // check shape tuple
930     unsigned int rval_nd;
931     unsigned int * rval_dims;
932     size_t rval_size = 1;
933 
934     if (PyTuple_Check(shape)){
935         // copy shape to integer array
936         rval_nd = PyTuple_Size(shape);
937     }else if (PyInt_Check(shape)){
938         rval_nd = 1;
939     }else{
940         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "shape must be tuple of integers or an integer");
941         return NULL;
942     }
943     rval_dims = (unsigned int*)malloc(rval_nd * sizeof(int));
944 
945     if(PyTuple_Check(shape)){
946         for (int i = 0; i < rval_nd; ++i)
947         {
948             rval_dims[i] = PyInt_AsLong(PyTuple_GetItem(shape, i)); //GetItem returns borrowed reference
949             if (PyErr_Occurred()) //error in AsLong
950             {
951                 free(rval_dims);
952                 return NULL;
953             }
954             if(rval_dims[i]<0){
955                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "Reshape has invalid dimension %i (must be >=0)",rval_dims[i]);
956                 free(rval_dims);
957                 return NULL;
958             }
959             rval_size = rval_size * rval_dims[i];
960         }
961     }else{
962         rval_size = PyInt_AsLong(shape);
963         rval_dims[0] = rval_size;
964     }
965     // calculate new size, assert same as old size
966     if (rval_size != CudaNdarray_SIZE(self))
967     {
968         PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "size must remain unchanged, changed from %lld to %lld", CudaNdarray_SIZE(self), rval_size);
969         free(rval_dims);
970         return NULL;
971     }
972     if (rval_size==0)
973     {
974         PyObject * rval = CudaNdarray_NewDims(rval_nd, rval_dims);
975         free(rval_dims);
976         return rval;
977     }
978 
979     //return a view, not a copy
980     //we can do this as we checked self is c_contiguous
981     CudaNdarray * rval = (CudaNdarray * )CudaNdarray_New(rval_nd);
982 
983     if (!rval || 0 != rval->data_allocated
984         ||CudaNdarray_set_device_data(rval, CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self), self))
985     {
986         Py_XDECREF(rval);
987         free(rval_dims);
988         return NULL;
989     }
990     //set dim and stride
991     int size = 1;
992     for (int i = rval_nd-1; i >= 0; --i)
993     {
994         CudaNdarray_set_stride(rval, i, (rval_dims[i] == 1) ? 0 : size);
995         CudaNdarray_set_dim(rval, i, rval_dims[i]);
996         size = size * rval_dims[i];
997     }
998     free(rval_dims);
999     return (PyObject*)rval;
1000 }

1002 PyObject * CudaNdarray_View(const CudaNdarray * self)
1003 {
1004     CudaNdarray * rval = (CudaNdarray*)CudaNdarray_New(self->nd);
1005     if (!rval || CudaNdarray_set_device_data(rval, CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self), self))
1006     {
1007         Py_XDECREF(rval);
1008         rval = NULL;
1009     }
1010     else
1011     {
1012         for (int i = 0; i < self->nd; ++i)
1013         {
1014             CudaNdarray_set_dim(rval, i, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i]);
1015             CudaNdarray_set_stride(rval, i, CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[i]);
1016         }
1017     }
1018     return (PyObject*)rval;
1019 }

1021 /*
1022  * d0,... are the output dims
1023  * indices are a list of index to operate on
1024  *         They are int32 viewed as float32.
1025  * a is the output
1026  * b is the input
1027  * dB0, the source leading dimensions size
1028  */
1029 template <int operator_num>
1030 __global__ void k_take_3(const int d0, const int d1, const int d2,
1031                          const npy_int64* indices,
1032                          float* a,
1033                          const int sA0, const int sA1, const int sA2,
1034                          const float* b, const int dB0,
1035                          const int sB0, const int sB1, const int sB2,
1036                          int* err){
1037     for (int i0 = blockIdx.x; i0 < d0; i0 += gridDim.x){
1038         npy_int64 idx = indices[i0];
1039         if (idx<0)
1040             idx += dB0; // To allow negative indexing.
1041         if ((idx < 0) || (idx >= dB0)){
1042             // Any value other the 0 probably work. But to be more safe, I want
1043             // to change all bits to prevent problem with concurrent write that
1044             // could cross cache line. But this should not happen with the
1045             // current code and driver.
1046             *err = 0xFFFF;
1047             continue;
1048         }
1049         for (int i1 = threadIdx.x; i1 < d1; i1 += blockDim.x){
1050             for (int i2 = threadIdx.y; i2 < d2; i2 += blockDim.y){
1051                 int a_idx = i0*sA0 + i1*sA1 + i2*sA2;
1052                 int b_idx = idx*sB0 + i1*sB1 + i2*sB2;
1053                 a[a_idx] = b[b_idx];
1054             }
1055         }
1056     }
1057 }

1059 // We try to be similar to the PyArray_TakeFrom function
1060 //http://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy/reference/c-api.array.html
1061 //TODO: support other clip mode then raise(clip, wrap)
1062 //self is the input that we copy data from.
1063 //The indices that we receive MUST be an CudaNdarray(float32)
1064 //    that is in fact a view to int64 indices
1065 PyObject*
1066 CudaNdarray_TakeFrom(CudaNdarray * self, PyObject *args){
1067     int verbose = 0;
1068     PyObject * indices_obj = NULL;
1069     //int axis; Default None, that mean the flattened array.
1070     PyObject * axis_obj = Py_None;
1071     PyObject * out_obj = Py_None;
1072     PyObject * clipmode_obj = NULL;
1073     int max_threads = 1; // max threads per blocks
1074 
1075     if (! PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "O|OOOi", &indices_obj, &axis_obj,
1076                            &out_obj, &clipmode_obj, &max_threads))
1077         return NULL;
1078 
1079     //Check argument indices
1080     //TODO: if not a numpy.ndarray, convert to numpy.ndarray
1081     //TODO: If a CudaNdarray, accept it and suppose the data is int32? is float32 number of int?
1082     //TODO: Support ndarray of other dtype then int32
1083     //TODO: support list of indices that are not c_contiguous
1084     CudaNdarray * indices = NULL;
1085     if (CudaNdarray_Check(indices_obj)) {
1086         if (verbose) printf("cudandarray indices\n");
1087         indices = (CudaNdarray*) indices_obj;
1088         Py_INCREF(indices);
1089     } else if (PyArray_Check(indices_obj)) {
1090         if (verbose) printf("ndarray indices\n");
1091         if (PyArray_TYPE((PyArrayObject *)indices_obj) != NPY_INT64) {
1092             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
1093                             "CudaNdarray_TakeFrom: need a ndarray for indices"
1094                             " with dtype int64");
1095             return NULL;
1096         }
1097         if (PyArray_NDIM(((PyArrayObject*)indices_obj)) != 1) {
1098             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
1099                             "CudaNdarray_TakeFrom: need a CudaNdarray of"
1100                             " indices with only 1 dimensions");
1101             return NULL;
1102         }
1103         // We need indices_obj to be contiguous, in order to take a view
1104         // with a different dtype.
1105         if (!PyArray_IS_C_CONTIGUOUS((PyArrayObject*) indices_obj)) {
1106             PyObject* indices_obj_contig = PyArray_NewCopy((PyArrayObject*) indices_obj, NPY_CORDER);
1107             if (!indices_obj_contig)
1108                 return NULL;
1109             indices_obj = indices_obj_contig;
1110         } else {
1111             // Keep the refcount consistent
1112             Py_INCREF(indices_obj);
1113         }
1114         PyArray_Descr* float32_descr = PyArray_DescrFromType(NPY_FLOAT32);
1115         PyObject * indices_float32 = NULL;
1116         indices_float32 = PyArray_View((PyArrayObject*)indices_obj,
1117                                                   float32_descr, NULL);
1118         if (verbose) printf("ndarray indices\n");
1119         if (!indices_float32) {
1120             Py_DECREF(indices_obj);
1121             return NULL;
1122         }
1123 
1124         indices = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_New();
1125         if (verbose) printf("\nndarray after new\n");
1126         if (! indices){
1127             Py_DECREF(indices_obj);
1128             Py_DECREF(indices_float32);
1129             return NULL;
1130         }
1131         if (CudaNdarray_CopyFromArray(indices,
1132                                       (PyArrayObject *)indices_float32)){
1133             Py_DECREF(indices_obj);
1134             Py_DECREF(indices_float32);
1135             return NULL;
1136         }
1137         Py_DECREF(indices_obj);
1138         Py_DECREF(indices_float32);
1139     } else {
1140         PyObject* py_s = PyObject_Str(indices_obj);
1141         const char* s = PyString_AsString(py_s);
1142         Py_DECREF(py_s);
1143         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError,
1144                      "CudaNdarray_TakeFrom: need an ndarray of int64 or a"
1145                      " CudaNdarray(float32) that is a view from int64 data"
1146                      " for indices. Got %s", s);
1147         return NULL;
1148     }
1149 
1150     if (verbose) {
1151         printf("indices used on the gpu\n");
1152         fprint_CudaNdarray(stdout, indices);
1153         PyObject * used_indices = CudaNdarray_CreateArrayObj(indices);
1154         PyObject_Print(used_indices, stdout, 0);
1155         Py_DECREF(used_indices);
1156     }
1157     if (verbose) printf("after print of object\n");
1158     if(!CudaNdarray_is_c_contiguous(indices) != 0) {
1159         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_NotImplementedError,
1160                         "CudaNdarray_TakeFrom: The indices must be contiguous in memory.");
1161         Py_DECREF(indices);
1162         return NULL;
1163     }
1164     int nb_indices = CudaNdarray_SIZE((CudaNdarray *)indices) / 2;// int64 are 8 bytes, float32 are 4 bytes
1165 
1166     //Check argument axis
1167     //TODO: implement the default and other axis
1168     long axis = PyInt_AsLong(axis_obj);
1169 
1170     if (axis != 0) {
1171         PyErr_Format(PyExc_NotImplementedError,
1172                      "CudaNdarray_TakeFrom: only axis=0 is currently supported."
1173                      " Got %ld.", axis);
1174         Py_DECREF(indices);
1175         return NULL;
1176     }
1177 
1178     //Check argument out_obj
1179     CudaNdarray * out = NULL;
1180     if (out_obj && CudaNdarray_Check(out_obj))
1181         out = (CudaNdarray*) out_obj;
1182     if (out && (out->nd != self->nd ||
1183                 CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(out)[0] != nb_indices))
1184         out = NULL;
1185     int * dims = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * self->nd);
1186     dims[0] = nb_indices;
1187 
1188     for (int i=1 ; i<self->nd ; i++) {
1189         dims[i] = CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i];
1190         if (out && CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(out)[i] != dims[i]) {
1191             out = NULL;
1192         }
1193     }
1194     if (!out) {
1195         out = (CudaNdarray*)CudaNdarray_New();
1196         if (!out){
1197             Py_DECREF(indices);
1198             free(dims);
1199             return NULL;
1200         }
1201         if (CudaNdarray_alloc_contiguous(out, self->nd, dims)) {
1202             Py_DECREF(out);
1203             Py_DECREF(indices);
1204             free(dims);
1205             return NULL;
1206         }
1207     }else {
1208         Py_INCREF(out);
1209     }
1210 
1211     //Check argument clipmode
1212     if (clipmode_obj) {
1213         char * clipmode = PyString_AsString(clipmode_obj);
1214         if (! clipmode){
1215             Py_DECREF(indices);
1216             Py_DECREF(out);
1217             free(dims);
1218             return NULL;
1219         }
1220         if (strcmp(clipmode, "raise") != 0) {
1221             PyErr_Format(PyExc_NotImplementedError,
1222                          "CudaNdarray_TakeFrom: only the raise mode is currently supported. Got '%s'",
1223                          clipmode);
1224             Py_DECREF(indices);
1225             Py_DECREF(out);
1226             free(dims);
1227             return NULL;
1228         }
1229     }
1230     void (*k3)(const int, const int, const int,
1231                const npy_int64*,
1232                float*, const int, const int, const int,
1233                const float*, const int,
1234                const int, const int, const int,
1235                int*);
1236     k3 = k_take_3<CPY>;
1237 
1238     // Create the memory place that will store the error information.
1239     if(init_err_var() != 0) return NULL;
1240 
1241     dim3 n_blocks(std::min(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(out)[0],65535),1,1);
1242     if(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(out)[0] == 0){
1243         // We take 0 elements, so no need for the rest of the code.
1244         // This speed up that case AND fix crash otherwise.
1245         free(dims);
1246         Py_DECREF(indices);
1247         return (PyObject *)out;
1248     }
1249 
1250     switch (self->nd) {
1251         case 1:
1252             {
1253                 dim3 n_threads(1, 1, 1);
1254                 if (verbose)
1255                     printf("cudaGetLastError=%d, nd=%d"
1256                            " kernel config: (n_blocks.x=%d, n_blocks.y=%d,"
1257                            " n_threads.x=%i, n_threads.y=%i)\n",
1258                            cudaGetLastError(), self->nd,
1259                            n_blocks.x, n_blocks.y, n_threads.x, n_threads.y);
1260                 k3<<<n_blocks, n_threads>>>(
1261                         dims[0],
1262                         1,
1263                         1,
1264                         (npy_int64*) CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(indices),
1265                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(out),
1266                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(out)[0], //strides
1267                         1,
1268                         1,
1269                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
1270                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0], //For indices check
1271                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0], //strides
1272                         1,
1273                         1,
1274                         err_var);
1275             }
1276             break;
1277         case 2:
1278             {
1279                 dim3 n_threads(std::min(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(out)[1], max_threads), 1, 1);
1280 
1281                 if (verbose)
1282                     printf("cudaGetLastError=%d, nd=%d"
1283                            " kernel config: (n_blocks.x=%d, n_blocks.y=%d,"
1284                            " n_threads.x=%i, n_threads.y=%i)\n",
1285                            cudaGetLastError(), self->nd,
1286                            n_blocks.x, n_blocks.y, n_threads.x, n_threads.y);
1287 
1288                 k3<<<n_blocks, n_threads>>>(
1289                         dims[0], //dimensions
1290                         dims[1],
1291                         1,
1292                         (npy_int64*) CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(indices),
1293                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(out),
1294                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(out)[0], //strides
1295                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(out)[1],
1296                         1,
1297                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
1298                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0], //For indices check
1299                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0], //strides
1300                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[1],
1301                         1,
1302                         err_var);
1303             }
1304             break;
1305         case 3:
1306             {
1307                 int ty = std::min(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(out)[2], max_threads);
1308                 int tx = std::min(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(out)[1], max_threads / ty);
1309                 dim3 n_threads(tx, ty, 1);
1310                 if (verbose)
1311                     printf("cudaGetLastError=%d, nd=%d"
1312                            " kernel config: (n_blocks.x=%d, n_blocks.y=%d,"
1313                            " n_threads.x=%i, n_threads.y=%i)\n",
1314                            cudaGetLastError(), self->nd,
1315                            n_blocks.x, n_blocks.y, n_threads.x, n_threads.y);
1316                 k3<<<n_blocks, n_threads>>>(
1317                         dims[0], //dimensions
1318                         dims[1],
1319                         dims[2],
1320                         (npy_int64*) CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(indices),
1321                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(out),
1322                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(out)[0], //strides
1323                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(out)[1],
1324                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(out)[2],
1325                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
1326                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0], //For indices check
1327                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0], //strides
1328                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[1],
1329                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[2],
1330                         err_var);
1331             }
1332             break;
1333     default:
1334         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_NotImplementedError,
1335                         "CudaNdarray_TakeFrom: only input with 1, 2 or 3"
1336                         " dimensions are currently supported");
1337 
1338     }
1339     free(dims);
1340     CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
1341     cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
1342     if (cudaSuccess != err) {
1343         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
1344                      "Cuda error: %s: %s.\n",
1345                      "CudaNdarray_TakeFrom",
1346                      cudaGetErrorString(err));
1347         Py_DECREF(indices);
1348         Py_DECREF(out);
1349         return NULL;
1350     }
1351 
1352     int index_err = check_err_var();
1353     Py_DECREF(indices);
1354     if (index_err != 0) {
1355         Py_DECREF(out);
1356         return NULL;
1357     }
1358 
1359     if (verbose) printf("TAKE SUCCEDED\n");
1360     return (PyObject *)out;
1361 }

1364 PyObject * CudaNdarray_SetStride(CudaNdarray * self, PyObject *args)
1365 {
1366     int pos, stride;
1367     if (! PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "ii", &pos, &stride))
1368         return NULL;
1369     if ((pos < 0) || (pos >= self->nd))
1370     {
1371         PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "position argument out of legal range [0, %i)", self->nd);
1372         return NULL;
1373     }
1374     CudaNdarray_set_stride(self, pos, stride);
1375     if (cnda_copy_structure_to_device(self))
1376     {
1377         return NULL;
1378     }
1379     Py_INCREF(Py_None);
1380     return Py_None;
1381 }

1393     if (cnda_copy_structure_to_device(self))

1402 CudaNdarray_exp(CudaNdarray* self)
1403 {
1404     CudaNdarray * rval = (CudaNdarray *)CudaNdarray_New();
1405     if ((NULL == rval) || CudaNdarray_alloc_contiguous(rval, self->nd, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)))
1406     {
1407         Py_XDECREF(rval);
1408         return NULL;
1409     }
1410     unsigned int size = 1;
1411     for (int i = 0; i < self->nd; i++)
1412     {
1413         size *= (unsigned int) CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i];
1414     }
1415     unsigned int threads_per_block = std::min(size, (unsigned int)NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK);
1416     unsigned int n_blocks = std::min(ceil_intdiv(size,threads_per_block), (unsigned int)NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS);
1417     k_elemwise_unary_rowmajor_exp<<<n_blocks,threads_per_block>>>(size, self->nd, CudaNdarray_DEV_DIMS(self),
1418             CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self), CudaNdarray_DEV_STRIDES(self),
1419             CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(rval), CudaNdarray_DEV_STRIDES(rval));
1420 
1421     //TODO: don't do this right away, do it when we need the result
1422     CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
1423     cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
1424     if( cudaSuccess != err)
1425     {
1426         Py_DECREF(rval);
1427         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError, "Cuda error: %s: %s.\n", "kExp", cudaGetErrorString(err));
1428         return NULL;
1429     }
1430 
1431     return (PyObject*)rval;
1432 }

1484 __global__ void kAdd_contiguous(float* a, float* b, float* dest, unsigned int numEls) {
1485     const unsigned int idx = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
1486     const unsigned int numThreads = blockDim.x * gridDim.x;
1487 
1488     for (unsigned int i = idx; i < numEls; i += numThreads) {
1489         dest[i] = a[i] + b[i];
1490     }
1491 }

1493 // Will be called by __add__ in Python
1494 static PyObject *
1495 CudaNdarray_add(PyObject* py_self, PyObject * py_other)
1496 {
1497     if (! CudaNdarray_Check(py_self)) {
1498         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "need a CudaNdarray on left");
1499         return NULL;
1500     }
1501     if (! CudaNdarray_Check(py_other)) {
1502         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "need a CudaNdarray on right");
1503         return NULL;
1504     }
1505     CudaNdarray * self = (CudaNdarray *)py_self;
1506     CudaNdarray * other = (CudaNdarray *)py_other;
1507     if(!CudaNdarray_is_c_contiguous(self) || !CudaNdarray_is_c_contiguous(other)){
1508         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "We have implementet only the c_contiguous version for now.");
1509         return NULL;
1510     }
1511 
1512     //standard elemwise size checks
1513     if (self->nd != other->nd)
1514     {
1515         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "CudaNdarray_add: need same number of dims");
1516         return NULL;
1517     }
1518     //standard elemwise dim checks
1519     unsigned int size = 1;
1520     for (int i = 0; i< self->nd; ++i)
1521     {
1522         if (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i] != CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(other)[i])
1523         {
1524             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "need same dimensions");
1525             return NULL;
1526         }
1527         size *= (unsigned int) CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i];
1528     }
1529     CudaNdarray * rval = (CudaNdarray *)CudaNdarray_New();
1530     if (!rval || CudaNdarray_alloc_contiguous(rval, self->nd, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)))
1531     {
1532         Py_XDECREF(rval);
1533         return NULL;
1534     }
1535 
1536     if(CudaNdarray_SIZE((CudaNdarray *)py_self)==0 && CudaNdarray_SIZE((CudaNdarray *)py_other)==0){
1537       return (PyObject *) rval;
1538     }
1539 
1540     int threads_per_block = std::min(size, (unsigned int)NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK);
1541     int n_blocks = std::min(ceil_intdiv(size,(unsigned int)threads_per_block), (unsigned int)NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS);
1542     kAdd_contiguous<<<n_blocks,threads_per_block>>>(
1543             self->devdata, other->devdata, rval->devdata, size);
1544     CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
1545     cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
1546     if( cudaSuccess != err)
1547     {
1548         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError, "Cuda error: %s: %s.\n", "kAdd", cudaGetErrorString(err));
1549         Py_DECREF(rval);
1550         return NULL;
1551     }
1552     return (PyObject *) rval;
1553 }

1555 template <int operator_num>
1556 __global__ void k_ielem_3(const int d0, const int d1, const int d2,
1557         float* a, const int sA0, const int sA1, const int sA2,
1558         const float* b, const int sB0, const int sB1, const int sB2){
1559     for (int i0 = blockIdx.x; i0 < d0; i0 += gridDim.x){
1560         for (int i1 = blockIdx.y; i1 < d1; i1 += gridDim.y){
1561             for (int i2 = threadIdx.x; i2 < d2; i2 += blockDim.x){
1562                 switch (operator_num)
1563                 {
1564                   case IADD:
1565                     a[i0*sA0 + i1*sA1 + i2*sA2] += b[i0*sB0 + i1*sB1 + i2*sB2];
1566                     break;
1567                   case IDIV:
1568                     a[i0*sA0 + i1*sA1 + i2*sA2] /= b[i0*sB0 + i1*sB1 + i2*sB2];
1569                     break;
1570                   case CPY:
1571                     a[i0*sA0 + i1*sA1 + i2*sA2] = b[i0*sB0 + i1*sB1 + i2*sB2];
1572                     break;
1573                 }
1574             }
1575         }
1576     }
1577 }

1582                          const int sA2, const int sA3,

1586         for (int i1 = blockIdx.y; i1 < d1; i1 += gridDim.y){
1587             for (int i2 = threadIdx.x; i2 < d2; i2 += blockDim.x){
1588                 for (int i3 = threadIdx.y; i3 < d3; i3 += blockDim.y){

1648 /*
1649 CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise
1650 Compute elemwise, working inplace on A.
1651 Currently implemented A / B, A + B and A = B
1652 (the last is not tested and not used!)
1653 
1654 py_self - the CudaNdarray that we'll modify (A)
1655 py_other - the other argument (B)
1656 fct_nb - which operation to perform (operator_t)
1657 
1658 Returns 0 on success.
1659 Returns -1 on failure, and sets Python exception.
1660 
1661 */
1662 int
1663 CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise(PyObject* py_self, PyObject * py_other, operator_t fct_nb)
1664 {
1665     int verbose = 0;
1666     void (*k3)(const int, const int, const int,
1667                     float*, const int, const int, const int,
1668                     const float*, const int, const int, const int);
1669     void (*k4)(const int, const int, const int, const int,
1670                     float*, const int, const int,
1671                     const int, const int,
1672                     const float*, const int, const int,
1673                     const int, const int);
1674     void (*k6)(const int, const int,
1675                const int, const int,
1676                const int, const int,
1677                float*, const int, const int,
1678                const int, const int,
1679                const int, const int,
1680                const float*, const int, const int,
1681                const int, const int,
1682                const int, const int);
1683     switch (fct_nb)
1684     {
1685         case IADD:
1686             k3 = k_ielem_3<IADD>;
1687             k4 = k_ielem_4<IADD>;
1688             k6 = k_ielem_6<IADD>;
1689             break;
1690         case IDIV:
1691             k3 = k_ielem_3<IDIV>;
1692             k4 = k_ielem_4<IDIV>;
1693             k6 = k_ielem_6<IDIV>;
1694             break;
1695         case CPY:
1696             k3 = k_ielem_3<CPY>;
1697             k4 = k_ielem_4<CPY>;
1698             k6 = k_ielem_6<CPY>;
1699             break;
1700         default:
1701             assert (0);
1702             PyErr_Format(
1703                 PyExc_TypeError,
1704                 "CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise invalid fct_nb (%i).",
1705                 (int)fct_nb);
1706             return -1;
1707     }
1708     if (!CudaNdarray_Check(py_self)) {
1709         PyErr_SetString(
1710             PyExc_TypeError,
1711             "CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise need a CudaNdarray on left");
1712         return -1;
1713     }
1714     CudaNdarray * new_other = NULL;
1715     if (!CudaNdarray_Check(py_other)) {
1716         new_other = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_New();
1717         if(!new_other)
1718         {
1719             return -1;
1720         }
1721         if(CudaNdarray_CopyFromArray(new_other, (PyArrayObject *) py_other))
1722         {
1723             Py_XDECREF(new_other);
1724             return -1;
1725         }
1726         py_other = (PyObject *) new_other;
1727     }
1728 
1729     CudaNdarray * self = (CudaNdarray *)py_self;
1730     CudaNdarray * other = (CudaNdarray *)py_other;
1731 
1732     if (verbose)
1733     {
1734         fprintf(stderr,
1735             "INPLACE ADD/DIV for self->nd=%d other->nd=%d\n",
1736             self->nd, other->nd);
1737     }
1738 
1739     //standard elemwise nb dim checks
1740     if (self->nd < other->nd)
1741     {
1742         PyErr_Format(
1743             PyExc_TypeError,
1744             "CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise: The destination need more or the"
1745             " same number of dimensions then the source. Got %d and %d.",
1746             self->nd, other->nd);
1747         Py_XDECREF(new_other);
1748         return -1;
1749     }
1750 
1751     //broadcast to the same number of dimensions.
1752     int* other_dims = (int*) alloca(self->nd * sizeof(int));
1753     int* other_strides = (int*) alloca(self->nd * sizeof(int));
1754     int added_dims = self->nd - other->nd;
1755     // Add the added broadcasted dimensions
1756     for (int i = 0; i< added_dims; ++i)
1757     {
1758         other_dims[i] = 1;
1759         other_strides[i] = 0;
1760     }
1761     // Copy the existing dimensions
1762     for (int i = 0; i< other->nd; ++i)
1763     {
1764         other_dims[i+added_dims] = CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(other)[i];
1765         other_strides[i+added_dims] = CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(other)[i];
1766     }
1767 
1768     //standard elemwise dim checks
1769     unsigned int size = 1;
1770     for (int i = 0; i< self->nd; ++i)
1771     {
1772         if ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i] != other_dims[i])
1773             && (other_dims[i] != 1))
1774         {
1775             PyErr_SetString(
1776                 PyExc_ValueError,
1777                 "CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise need same dimensions (or broadcastable dimension)");
1778             Py_XDECREF(new_other);
1779             return -1;
1780         }
1781         // if we're broadcasting other, then make sure it has stride 0
1782         assert ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i] == other_dims[i])
1783             || (other_strides[i] == 0));
1784         size *= (unsigned int) CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i];
1785     }
1786 
1787     if (size==0)
1788     {
1789         int other_size = CudaNdarray_SIZE((CudaNdarray *)py_other);
1790         if (!(other_size == 0 || other_size == 1))
1791         {
1792             PyErr_SetString(
1793                 PyExc_ValueError,
1794                 "CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise cannot work inplace on"
1795                 " un-initialized array when the new value have more than"
1796                 " 0 or 1 broadcastable dimensions");
1797             Py_XDECREF(new_other);
1798             return 0;
1799         }
1800         Py_XDECREF(new_other);
1801         return 0;
1802     }
1803 
1804     switch(self->nd)
1805     {
1806         case 0:
1807             {
1808                 dim3 n_blocks(1, 1, 1);
1809                 dim3 n_threads(1);
1810                 k3<<<n_blocks, n_threads>>>(
1811                         1, //d0
1812                         1, //d1
1813                         1, //d2
1814                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
1815                         1, //strides
1816                         1,
1817                         1,
1818                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(other),
1819                         1, //strides
1820                         1,
1821                         1);
1822                 CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
1823                 cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
1824                 if (cudaSuccess != err)
1825                 {
1826                     PyErr_Format(
1827                         PyExc_RuntimeError,
1828                         "CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise case0: Cuda error: %s: %s.\n",
1829                         "k3",
1830                         cudaGetErrorString(err));
1831                     Py_XDECREF(new_other);
1832                     return -1;
1833                 }
1834             }
1835             break;
1836         case 1:
1837             {
1838                 dim3 n_blocks(1, 1, 1);
1839                 dim3 n_threads(
1840                         std::min(
1841                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0],
1842                             NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK));
1843                 k3<<<n_blocks, n_threads>>>(
1844                         1, //dimensions
1845                         1,
1846                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0],
1847                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
1848                         1, //strides
1849                         1,
1850                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0],
1851                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(other),
1852                         1, //strides
1853                         1,
1854                         other_strides[0]);
1855                 CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
1856                 cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
1857                 if (cudaSuccess != err)
1858                 {
1859                     PyErr_Format(
1860                         PyExc_RuntimeError,
1861                         "CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise case1: Cuda error: %s: %s.\n",
1862                         "k3",
1863                         cudaGetErrorString(err));
1864                     Py_XDECREF(new_other);
1865                     return -1;
1866                 }
1867             }
1868             break;
1869         case 2:
1870             {
1871                 //TODO:  if both self and other are f-contiguous
1872                 //       Then flip the block and thread dimensions
1873                 //       to make contiguous reads & writes
1874                 dim3 n_blocks(1,
1875                         std::min(
1876                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0],
1877                             NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS));
1878                 dim3 n_threads(
1879                         std::min(
1880                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[1],
1881                             NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK));
1882                 k3<<<n_blocks, n_threads>>>(1,
1883                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0],
1884                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[1],
1885                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
1886                         1,
1887                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0],
1888                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[1],
1889                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(other),
1890                         1,
1891                         other_strides[0],
1892                         other_strides[1]);
1893                 CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
1894                 cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
1895                 if (cudaSuccess != err)
1896                 {
1897                     PyErr_Format(
1898                         PyExc_RuntimeError,
1899                         "CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise case2: Cuda error: %s: %s.\n",
1900                         "k3",
1901                         cudaGetErrorString(err));
1902                     Py_XDECREF(new_other);
1903                     return -1;
1904                 }
1905             }
1906             break;
1907         case 3:
1908             {
1909                 //TODO:  Dimshuffle so that at least one of the arrays
1910                 //       has a contiguous dimension on the thread idx.
1911                 dim3 n_blocks(
1912                         std::min(
1913                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0],
1914                             NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS),
1915                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[1]);
1916                 while (n_blocks.x * n_blocks.y > NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS)
1917                     n_blocks.y /= 2;
1918                 dim3 n_threads(
1919                         std::min(
1920                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[2],
1921                             NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK));
1922                 k3<<<n_blocks, n_threads>>>(
1923                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0],
1924                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[1],
1925                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[2],
1926                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
1927                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0],
1928                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[1],
1929                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[2],
1930                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(other),
1931                         other_strides[0],
1932                         other_strides[1],
1933                         other_strides[2]);
1934                 CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
1935                 cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
1936                 if (cudaSuccess != err)
1937                 {
1938                     PyErr_Format(
1939                         PyExc_RuntimeError,
1940                         "CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise case3: Cuda error: %s: %s.\n",
1941                         "k3",
1942                         cudaGetErrorString(err));
1943                     Py_XDECREF(new_other);
1944                     return -1;
1945                 }
1946             }
1947             break;
1948         case 4:
1949             {
1950                 dim3 n_blocks(
1951                         std::min(
1952                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0],
1953                             NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS),
1954                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[1]
1955                         );
1956                 while (n_blocks.x * n_blocks.y > NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS)
1957                     n_blocks.y /= 2;
1958                 dim3 n_threads(
1959                         std::min(
1960                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[2],
1961                             NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK)
1962                     //TODO: DON"T YOU NEED OT PUT DIMS[3] in here???
1963                             );
1964                 k4<<<n_blocks, n_threads>>>(
1965                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0],
1966                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[1],
1967                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[2],
1968                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[3],
1969                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
1970                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0],
1971                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[1],
1972                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[2],
1973                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[3],
1974                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(other),
1975                         other_strides[0],
1976                         other_strides[1],
1977                         other_strides[2],
1978                         other_strides[3]);
1979                 CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
1980                 cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
1981                 if (cudaSuccess != err)
1982                 {
1983                     PyErr_Format(
1984                         PyExc_RuntimeError,
1985                         "CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise case4: Cuda error: %s: %s.\n",
1986                         "k4",
1987                         cudaGetErrorString(err));
1988                     Py_XDECREF(new_other);
1989                     return -1;
1990                 }
1991             }
1992             break;
1993         case 5:
1994             {
1995                 dim3 n_blocks(
1996                         std::min(
1997                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[1],
1998                             NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS),
1999                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[2]);
2000                 while (n_blocks.x * n_blocks.y > NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS)
2001                     n_blocks.y /= 2;
2002                 dim3 n_threads(
2003                         std::min(
2004                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[3],
2005                             NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK)
2006                     //TODO: DON"T YOU NEED OT PUT DIMS[3] in here???
2007                     );
2008                 for (int i = 0; i < CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0]; ++i)
2009                 {
2010                      k4<<<n_blocks, n_threads>>>(
2011                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[1],
2012                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[2],
2013                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[3],
2014                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[4],
2015                             CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self) + i * CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0],
2016                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[1],
2017                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[2],
2018                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[3],
2019                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[4],
2020                             CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(other) + i * other_strides[0],
2021                             other_strides[1],
2022                             other_strides[2],
2023                             other_strides[3],
2024                             other_strides[4]);
2025                     CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
2026                     cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
2027                     if( cudaSuccess != err)
2028                     {
2029                         PyErr_Format(
2030                             PyExc_RuntimeError,
2031                             "CudaNdarray_inplace_elemwise case5: Cuda error: %s: %s. n_block=(%ld,%ld) n_threads=%ld\n",
2032                             "k5 with loop over k4",
2033                             cudaGetErrorString(err),
2034                             (long) n_blocks.x, (long) n_blocks.y, (long) n_threads.x);
2035                         Py_XDECREF(new_other);
2036                         return -1;
2037                     }
2038                 }
2039             }
2040             break;
2041         case 6:
2042             {
2043                 dim3 n_blocks(
2044                         std::min(
2045                             CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0],
2046                             NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS),
2047                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[1],
2048                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[2]
2049                         );
2050                 while (n_blocks.x * n_blocks.y > NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS)
2051                     n_blocks.y /= 2;
2052                 // GTX285(compute capabilities 1.3) don't support n_blocks.z > 1
2053                 // (compute capabilities 2.0) support 65535 for n_blocks.z
2054                 //while (n_blocks.x * n_blocks.y * n_blocks.z > NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS)
2055                 //    n_blocks.z /= 2;
2056                 n_blocks.z = 1;
2057                 dim3 n_threads(

2067                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[2],
2068                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[3],
2069                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[4],
2070                         CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[5],
2071                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
2072                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0],
2073                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[1],
2074                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[2],
2075                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[3],
2076                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[4],
2077                         CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[5],
2078                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(other),
2079                         other_strides[0],
2080                         other_strides[1],
2081                         other_strides[2],
2082                         other_strides[3],
2083                         other_strides[4],
2084                         other_strides[5]);
2085                 CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
2086                 cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
2087                 if (cudaSuccess != err)
2088                 {
2089                     PyErr_Format(
2090                         PyExc_RuntimeError,

2092                         "k6",
2093                         cudaGetErrorString(err),
2094                         (long) n_blocks.x, (long) n_blocks.y, (long) n_blocks.z,
2095                         (long) n_threads.x);

2099             }
2100             break;
2101         default:
2102         {
2103             PyErr_Format(
2104                 PyExc_NotImplementedError,
2105                 "inplace_elemwise w nd=%i\n",
2106                 self->nd);
2107             Py_XDECREF(new_other);
2108             return -1;
2109         }
2110     }
2111     if (verbose)
2112         fprintf(stderr, "INPLACE ADD/DIV end\n");
2113     Py_XDECREF(new_other);
2114     return 0;
2115 }
