2264 // Will by called by __getitem__ in Python
2265 PyObject *
2266 CudaNdarray_Subscript(PyObject * py_self, PyObject * key)
2267 {
2268     int verbose = 0;
2269     if (verbose) fprintf(stderr, "Subscript .... \n");
2270     CudaNdarray * self = (CudaNdarray*) py_self;
2271     PyObject * py_rval = NULL;
2272     CudaNdarray * rval = NULL;
2273     PyObject * intobj = NULL;
2274 
2275     //PyObject_Print(key, stderr, 0);
2276 
2277     if (key == Py_Ellipsis)
2278     {
2279         Py_INCREF(py_self);
2280         return py_self;
2281     }
2282     if ((intobj=PyNumber_Int(key))) //INDEXING BY INTEGER
2283     //else if (PyInt_Check(key)) //INDEXING BY INTEGER
2284     {
2285         int d_idx = PyInt_AsLong(intobj);
2286         Py_DECREF(intobj); intobj=NULL;
2287         //int d_idx = PyInt_AsLong(key);
2288         if (self->nd == 0)
2289         {
2290             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_IndexError, "0-d arrays can't be indexed");
2291             return NULL;
2292         }
2293         int d_dim = CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0];
2294         int offset = 0;
2295 
2296         if ((d_idx >= 0) && (d_idx < d_dim))
2297         {
2298             //normal indexing
2299             offset += d_idx * CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0];
2300         }
2301         else if ((d_idx < 0) && (d_idx >= -d_dim))
2302         {
2303             //end-based indexing
2304             // d_idx is negative
2305             offset += (d_dim + d_idx) * CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0];
2306         }
2307         else
2308         {
2309             PyErr_Format(PyExc_IndexError,
2310                          "index out of bounds. Asked %d, but size of %d",
2311                          d_idx, d_dim);
2312             return NULL;
2313         }
2314 
2315         //allocate our subtensor view
2316         py_rval = CudaNdarray_new_nd(self->nd - 1);
2317         rval = (CudaNdarray*) py_rval;
2318         if (!rval) return NULL;
2319         assert (0 == rval->data_allocated);
2320 
2321         //initialize the view's data pointer to our own.
2322         if (CudaNdarray_set_device_data(rval, CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self) + offset, self))
2323         {
2324             Py_DECREF(rval);
2325             return NULL;
2326         }
2327         for (int d = 1; d < self->nd; ++d)
2328         {
2329             CudaNdarray_set_stride(rval, d-1, CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[d]);
2330             CudaNdarray_set_dim(rval, d-1, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[d]);
2331         }
2332     }
2333     else
2334     {
2335         PyErr_Clear();
2336     }
2337     if (PySlice_Check(key)) //INDEXING BY SLICE
2338     {
2339         if (verbose) fprintf(stderr, "by slice\n");
2340         if (self->nd == 0)
2341         {
2342             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "cannot slice a 0-d array");
2343             return NULL;
2344         }
2345 
2346         int d_dim = CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0];
2347         Py_ssize_t start, stop, step, slen;
2348         if (PySlice_GetIndicesEx(SLICE_CAST(key), d_dim, &start, &stop, &step, &slen))
2349         {
2350             if (verbose)
2351                 fprintf(stderr, "PySlice_GetIndicesEx failed\n");
2352             return NULL;
2353         }
2354         if (verbose)
2355         {
2356             std::cerr << "start " << start << "\n";
2357             std::cerr << "stop " << stop << "\n";
2358             std::cerr << "step " << step << "\n";
2359             std::cerr << "slen " << slen << "\n";
2360         }
2361 
2362         //allocate our subtensor view
2363         py_rval = CudaNdarray_new_nd(self->nd);
2364         rval = (CudaNdarray*) py_rval;
2365         if (!rval) return NULL;
2366         assert (0 == rval->data_allocated);
2367 
2368 
2369         //initialize the view's data pointer to our own.
2370         if (CudaNdarray_set_device_data(rval,
2371                     CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self) + start * CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0],
2372                     self))
2373         {
2374             Py_DECREF(rval);
2375             return NULL;
2376         }
2377         //initialize dimension 0 of rval
2378         CudaNdarray_set_stride(rval, 0,
2379                 (slen == 1) ? 0 : step * CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0]);
2380         CudaNdarray_set_dim(rval, 0, slen);
2381         if (verbose) std::cerr << "rval stride " << CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(rval)[0] << "\n";
2382         // initialize dimensions > 0 of rval
2383         for (int d = 1; d < self->nd; ++d)
2384         {
2385             CudaNdarray_set_stride(rval, d, CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[d]);
2386             CudaNdarray_set_dim(rval, d, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[d]);
2387         }
2388     }
2389     if (PyTuple_Check(key)) //INDEXING BY TUPLE
2390     {
2391         if (verbose) fprintf(stderr, "by tuple\n");
2392         //elements of the tuple can be either integers or slices
2393         //the dimensionality of the view we will return is diminished for each slice in the tuple
2394 
2395         if (PyTuple_Size(key) > self->nd)
2396         {
2397             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_IndexError, "index error");
2398             return NULL;
2399         }
2400 
2401         //calculate the number of dimensions in the return value
2402         int rval_nd = self->nd;
2403         for (int d = 0; d < PyTuple_Size(key); ++d)
2404         {
2405             //On some paltform PyInt_Check(<type 'numpy.int64'>) return true, other it return false.
2406             //So we use PyArray_IsAnyScalar that should covert everything.
2407             rval_nd -= PyArray_IsAnyScalar(PyTuple_GetItem(key, d));
2408         }
2409 
2410         //allocate our subtensor view
2411         py_rval = CudaNdarray_new_nd(rval_nd);
2412         rval = (CudaNdarray*) py_rval;
2413         if (!rval) return NULL;
2414         assert (0 == rval->data_allocated);
2415 
2416         //initialize the view's data pointer to our own.
2417         if (CudaNdarray_set_device_data(rval, CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self), self))
2418         {
2419             Py_DECREF(rval);
2420             return NULL;
2421         }
2422 
2423         // rval_d will refer to the current dimension in the rval.
2424         // It will not be incremented for integer keys, but will be incremented for slice
2425         // keys
2426         int rval_d = 0;
2427 
2428         for (int d = 0; d < self->nd; ++d)
2429         {
2430             // keys can be shorter than self->nd.
2431             // when that happens, it means that the remaining dimensions are "full slices"
2432             if (d >=PyTuple_Size(key))
2433             {
2434                 CudaNdarray_set_stride(rval, rval_d, CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[d]);
2435                 CudaNdarray_set_dim(rval, rval_d, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[d]);
2436                 ++rval_d;
2437             }
2438             else
2439             {
2440                 PyObject * key_d = PyTuple_GetItem(key, d);
2441 
2442                 if (PySlice_Check(key_d))
2443                 {
2444                     Py_ssize_t start, stop, step, slen;
2445                     if (PySlice_GetIndicesEx(SLICE_CAST(key_d), CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[d], &start, &stop, &step, &slen))
2446                     {
2447                         Py_DECREF(rval);
2448                         return NULL;
2449                     }
2450                     rval->devdata += start * CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[d];
2451                     CudaNdarray_set_stride(rval, rval_d,
2452                             (slen == 1) ? 0 : step * CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[d]);
2453                     CudaNdarray_set_dim(rval, rval_d, slen);
2454                     if (0)
2455                     {
2456                         std::cerr << "start " << start << "\n";
2457                         std::cerr << "stop " << stop << "\n";
2458                         std::cerr << "step " << step << "\n";
2459                         std::cerr << "slen " << slen << "\n";
2460                     }
2461                     ++rval_d;
2462                 }
2463                 else if ((intobj=PyNumber_Int(key_d)))
2464                 {
2465                     assert(PyArray_IsAnyScalar(key_d));
2466                     int d_idx = PyInt_AsLong(intobj);
2467                     Py_DECREF(intobj);
2468                     intobj = NULL;
2469                     int d_dim = CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[d];
2470 
2471                     if ((d_idx >= 0) && (d_idx < d_dim))
2472                     {
2473                         //normal indexing
2474                         rval->devdata += d_idx * CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[d];
2475                     }
2476                     else if ((d_idx < 0) && (d_idx >= -d_dim))
2477                     {
2478                         //end-based indexing
2479                         rval->devdata += (d_dim + d_idx) * CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[d];
2480                     }
2481                     else
2482                     {
2483                         PyErr_Format(PyExc_IndexError,
2484                                      "index out of bounds. Asked %d for dimensions %d, but size of %d",
2485                                      d_idx, d, d_dim);
2486                         Py_DECREF(rval);
2487                         return NULL;
2488                     }
2489                 }
2490                 else
2491                 {
2492                     PyErr_Clear(); // clear the error set by PyNumber_Int
2493                     PyErr_SetString(PyExc_IndexError, "index must be either int or slice");
2494                     Py_DECREF(rval);
2495                     return NULL;
2496                 }
2497             }
2498         }
2499     }
2500     if (py_rval)
2501     {
2502         if (verbose) fprint_CudaNdarray(stderr, self);
2503         if (verbose) fprint_CudaNdarray(stderr, rval);
2504     }
2505     else
2506     {
2507         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_NotImplementedError, "Unknown key type");
2508         return NULL;
2509     }
2510     return py_rval;
2511 }

2513 // Will by called by __setitem__ in Python
2514 // See http://docs.python.org/dev/py3k/c-api/object.html#PyObject_SetItem
2515 // Doesn't handle broadcasting, e.g. a[:] = 5
2516 // Can only be assigned from a CudaNdarray on the right side
2517 // Or a ndarray
2518 // Or a python scalar with value 0 when the left side part is c contiguous.
2519 static int
2520 CudaNdarray_setitem(PyObject *o, PyObject  *key, PyObject  *value)
2521 {
2522     int verbose = 0;
2523     if (verbose) fprintf(stderr, "CudaNdarray_setitem start\n");
2524     // We try to copy directly into this CudaNdarray from the ndarray
2525     CudaNdarray* rval = (CudaNdarray*)CudaNdarray_Subscript(o, key);
2526     CudaNdarray* new_value = NULL;
2527 
2528     if(!rval){
2529         // CudaNdarray_Subscript failed and set the error msg.
2530         Py_XDECREF(rval);
2531         return -1;
2532     }
2533 
2534     if(rval != (CudaNdarray*)o &&
2535                 (rval->data_allocated ||
2536                  // The new array should have a base
2537                  !(((CudaNdarray*)rval)->base) ||
2538                  // If the original array has no base, the base of the new
2539                  // array should be the original one
2540                  (!((CudaNdarray*)o)->base && ((CudaNdarray*)rval)->base != o) ||
2541                  // Else, the two arrays should have the same base
2542                  (((CudaNdarray*)o)->base && ((CudaNdarray*)rval)->base != ((CudaNdarray*)o)->base)))
2543     {
2544         // This case shouldn't happen, based on what I see in Subscript
2545         // but just in case it happens sometime in the future
2546 
2547         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
2548                      "__getitem__ must return a CudaNdarray that refers to"
2549                      " the original CudaNdarray, not a copy. rval.base=%p"
2550                      " o.base=%p o=%p",
2551                      (((CudaNdarray*)rval)->base), ((CudaNdarray*)o)->base, o);
2552         Py_DECREF(rval);
2553         return -1;
2554     }
2555 
2556     PyObject * intobj = NULL;
2557     if (CudaNdarray_Check(o)  && PyArray_Check(value)){
2558         if (verbose)
2559             fprintf(stderr,
2560                     "CudaNdarray_setitem dest is a CudaNdarray and"
2561                     " value is a ndarray\n");
2562         new_value = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_New();
2563         if(!new_value)
2564         {
2565             return -1;
2566         }
2567         if (CudaNdarray_CopyFromArray(new_value, (PyArrayObject *) value))
2568         {
2569             Py_XDECREF(new_value);
2570             Py_XDECREF(rval);
2571             return -1;
2572         }
2573         value = (PyObject *) new_value;
2574     }
2575     else if ((intobj=PyNumber_Int(value)))
2576     {
2577         if (verbose)
2578             fprintf(stderr,
2579                     "CudaNdarray_setitem dest and value is a python number\n");
2580         if(! CudaNdarray_is_c_contiguous(rval)){
2581             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_NotImplementedError,
2582                  "CudaNdarray.__setitem__: When the new value is a scalar"
2583                  " of value 0 the part where we copy to must be c contiguous.");
2584             Py_XDECREF(rval);
2585             return -1;
2586         }
2587 
2588         long val = PyInt_AsLong(intobj);
2589         Py_DECREF(intobj); intobj=NULL;
2590         if (val == 0)
2591         {
2592             cudaError_t err = cudaMemset(rval->devdata, 0,
2593                                          CudaNdarray_SIZE(rval) * sizeof(real));
2594             Py_XDECREF(rval);
2595             if (err)
2596             {
2597                 // Clear the error flag, cudaMemset doesn't do it.
2598                 // Currently this returns the same thing as err, but if in future
2599                 // it returns something else I still don't see why we should ignore
2600                 // it.  All we want to do here is reset the flag.
2601                 cudaGetLastError();
2602                 PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError,
2603                                 "CudaNdarray.__setitem__: cudaMemset failed");
2604                 return -1;
2605             }
2606             return 0;
2607         } else {
2608             Py_XDECREF(rval);
2609             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_NotImplementedError,
2610                   "CudaNdarray.__setitem__: we support setting only python"
2611                   " scalar of value 0, numpy nd array and CudaNdarray.");
2612                 return -1;
2613         }
2614     }
2615 
2616     PyErr_Clear(); // clear PyNumber_Int error.
2617 
2618     if(!CudaNdarray_Check(o) || !CudaNdarray_Check(value))
2619     {
2620         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
2621           "CudaNdarray.__setitem__: left must be a CudaNdarrays and right"
2622           " must be a CudaNdarrays, an ndarray or a python scalar of value 0.");
2623         Py_XDECREF(new_value);
2624         return -1;
2625     }
2626 
2627     if (verbose)
2628         fprintf(stderr, "CudaNdarray_setitem dest and value are CudaNdarray\n");
2629 
2630     if (cnda_copy_structure_to_device(rval))
2631     {
2632         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError,
2633                 "CudaNdarray.__setitem__: syncing structure to device failed");
2634         Py_DECREF(rval);
2635         Py_XDECREF(new_value);
2636 
2637         if (verbose)
2638             fprintf(stderr, "CudaNdarray_setitem error end\n");
2639         return -1;
2640     }
2641 
2642     PyObject *baseSavedForComparison = rval->base;
2643 
2644     if (CudaNdarray_CopyFromCudaNdarray(rval, (CudaNdarray*)value, true))
2645     {
2646         Py_DECREF((PyObject*)rval);
2647         Py_XDECREF(new_value);
2648 
2649         if (verbose)
2650             fprintf(stderr, "CudaNdarray_setitem error end\n");
2651         return -1;
2652     }
2653 
2654     assert (rval->base == baseSavedForComparison);
2655     assert (rval->dev_structure_fresh);
2656 
2657     // Clean up locally-created references
2658     Py_DECREF(rval);
2659     Py_XDECREF(new_value);
2660 
2661     return 0;
2662 }

2669 };

2724 static int
2725 CudaNdarray_set_strides(CudaNdarray *self, PyObject *value, void *closure)
2726 {
2727     //npy_intp newstrides_bytes[PyTuple_Size(value)];
2728     if (PyTuple_Check(value)){
2729         if (PyTuple_Size(value) != CudaNdarray_NDIM(self)){
2730             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
2731                             "The new strides tuple must have the same length"
2732                             " as the number of dimensions");
2733             return -1;
2734         }
2735     }else if (PyList_Check(value)){
2736         if (PyList_Size(value) != CudaNdarray_NDIM(self)){
2737             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
2738                             "The new strides list must have the same length"
2739                             " as the number of dimensions");
2740             return -1;
2741         }
2742     }else{
2743         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError,
2744                         "The new strides need to be encoded in a tuple or list");
2745         return -1;
2746     }
2747     npy_intp* newstrides = (npy_intp*) alloca(CudaNdarray_NDIM(self) * sizeof(npy_intp));
2748     if (PyTuple_Check(value)){
2749         for(int i=0; i < CudaNdarray_NDIM(self); i++){
2750             newstrides[i] = PyInt_AsLong(PyTuple_GetItem(value, Py_ssize_t(i)));
2751             //newstrides_bytes[i] = newstrides[i] * 4;
2752         }
2753     }else if (PyList_Check(value)){
2754         for(int i=0; i < CudaNdarray_NDIM(self); i++){
2755             newstrides[i] = PyInt_AsLong(PyList_GetItem(value, Py_ssize_t(i)));
2756             //newstrides_bytes[i] = newstrides[i] * 4;
2757         }
2758     }
2759     /*
2760     // Do not do this check, as ExtractDiag needs that, and NumPy does not seem
2761     // to do it.
2762     npy_intp dims[PyTuple_Size(value)];
2763     for(int i=0; i < CudaNdarray_NDIM(self); i++){
2764         dims[i] = CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i];
2765     }
2766     if (!PyArray_CheckStrides(4,
2767                               CudaNdarray_NDIM(self),
2768                               0, 0,
2769                               dims,
2770                               newstrides_bytes)){        
2771         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "bad new strides");
2772         free(newstrides);
2773         return -1;
2774         }
2775     */
2776     for(int i=0; i < CudaNdarray_NDIM(self); i++){
2777         CudaNdarray_set_stride(self, i, newstrides[i]);
2778     }
2779     free(newstrides);
2780     return 0;
2781 }

2828 void put_in_dict(PyObject * dict, const char * key, int val)
2829 {
2830   PyObject * k = PyString_FromString(key);
2831   PyObject * v = PyInt_FromLong(val);
2832   PyDict_SetItem(dict, k, v);
2833   Py_DECREF(k);
2834   Py_DECREF(v);
2835 }

2837 PyObject *
2838 GetDeviceProperties(PyObject* _unused, PyObject* args)
2839 {
2840   int dev_id = -1;
2841   if (! PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "i", &dev_id))
2842     return NULL;
2843   cudaDeviceProp deviceProp;
2844   cudaGetDeviceProperties(&deviceProp, dev_id);
2845 
2846   PyObject * dict = PyDict_New();
2847   PyObject * str= PyString_FromString("name");
2848   PyObject * i = PyString_FromString(deviceProp.name);
2849   PyDict_SetItem(dict, str, i);
2850   Py_DECREF(str);
2851   Py_DECREF(i);
2852 
2853   put_in_dict(dict, "major", deviceProp.major);
2854   put_in_dict(dict, "minor", deviceProp.minor);
2855 #if CUDART_VERSION >= 2020
2856   int driverVersion = 0, runtimeVersion = 0;
2857   cudaDriverGetVersion(&driverVersion);
2858   cudaRuntimeGetVersion(&runtimeVersion);
2859   put_in_dict(dict, "driverVersion", driverVersion);
2860   put_in_dict(dict, "runtimeVersion", runtimeVersion);
2861 #endif
2862 #if CUDART_VERSION >= 2000
2863 
2864   put_in_dict(dict, "multiProcessorCount", deviceProp.multiProcessorCount);
2865   //if ConvertSMVer2Cores is not defined in cuda_runtime_api.h, the run time is too old.
2866   int sm_cores = -1;
2867   if(deviceProp.major==1)
2868     sm_cores = 32;
2869   else if(deviceProp.major==2 && deviceProp.minor==0)
2870     sm_cores = 32;
2871   else if(deviceProp.major==2 && deviceProp.minor==1)
2872     sm_cores = 48;
2873   put_in_dict(dict, "coresCount", sm_cores * deviceProp.multiProcessorCount);
2874 #endif
2875   put_in_dict(dict, "totalConstMem", deviceProp.totalConstMem);
2876   put_in_dict(dict, "sharedMemPerBlock", deviceProp.sharedMemPerBlock);
2877   put_in_dict(dict, "regsPerBlock", deviceProp.regsPerBlock);
2878   put_in_dict(dict, "warpSize", deviceProp.warpSize);

2912 /*
2913  * Returns in *free and *total respectively, the free and total amount of memory available for allocation by the device in bytes.
2914  */
2915 PyObject *
2916 GetDeviceMemInfo(PyObject* _unused, PyObject* dummy)
2917 {
2918     size_t free = 0, total = 0;
2919     if(g_gpu_context_active == 0){
2920         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError, "No gpu device selected yet. Please make sure the gpu device was initialized by Theano before.");
2921         return NULL;
2922     }
2923 
2924     cudaError_t err = cudaMemGetInfo(&free, &total);
2925     if (err != cudaSuccess){
2926         // Clear the error flag, cudaMemGetInfo doesn't do it.
2927         // Currently this returns the same thing as err, but if in future
2928         // it returns something else I still don't see why we should ignore
2929         // it.  All we want to do here is reset the flag.
2930         cudaGetLastError();
2931         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
2932                      "Error while getting memory info about the gpu: %s",
2933                      cudaGetErrorString(err));
2934         return NULL;
2935     }
2936     return PyTuple_Pack(2, PyLong_FromLong(free), PyLong_FromLong(total));
2937 }

3130 PyObject *
3131 CudaNdarray_ptr_int_size(PyObject* _unused, PyObject* args)
3132 {
3133     int *gpu_data = (int*)device_malloc(sizeof(int)*2);
3134     if(gpu_data == NULL){
3135         return NULL;
3136     }
3137     get_gpu_ptr_size<<<1,1>>>(gpu_data);
3138 
3139     cudaError_t cudaErr = cudaGetLastError();
3140     if (cudaSuccess != cudaErr){
3141 
3142         device_free(gpu_data);
3143         return PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
3144                             "CudaNdarray_ptr_int_size: error when calling the gpu code. (%s)",
3145                             cudaGetErrorString(cudaErr));
3146     }
3147 
3148     // Transfer the result to cpu
3149     int gpu_sizes[] = {-1,-1};
3150     cublasStatus_t err;
3151     err = cublasGetVector(2, sizeof(int), gpu_data, 1, gpu_sizes, 1);
3152     device_free(gpu_data);
3153 
3154     if (CUBLAS_STATUS_SUCCESS != err){
3155         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "error copying data to from memory");
3156         return NULL;
3157     }
3158     return Py_BuildValue("iiii", (int) gpu_sizes[0], (int)sizeof(float*),
3159                          (int)sizeof(int), (int) gpu_sizes[1]);
3160 }

3162 static int cublas_init();
3163 static void cublas_shutdown();
3164 // Initialize the gpu.
3165 // Takes two optional parameters, the device number and if we should use cnmem.
3166 // If the device number is provided, it sets that device to be the active device.
3167 // If not provided (usually just to test whether the gpu is available at all),
3168 // it does not set an active device.
3169 // Raises EnvironmentError or ValueError (as appropriate) if the initialization failed.
3170 // cnmem is threaded like a bool. If converted to 0, don't use cnmem. Otherwise, use it.
3171 PyObject *
3172 CudaNdarray_gpu_init(PyObject* _unused, PyObject* args)
3173 {
3174     int card_nb = 0;
3175     int card_number_provided = 1;
3176     float cnmem = 0; // Theano flag lib.cnmem
3177     // if we're given something wildly invalid, this will throw a TypeError
3178     if(!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "|if", &card_nb, &cnmem))
3179         return NULL;
3180     if(cnmem)
3181         g_use_cnmem = true;
3182 
3183     if(PyTuple_Size(args) == 0) {
3184         card_number_provided = 0;
3185         card_nb = 0;
3186     }
3187 
3188     int deviceCount;
3189     cudaError err = cudaGetDeviceCount(&deviceCount);
3190     if(cudaSuccess != err) {
3191         return PyErr_Format(PyExc_EnvironmentError,
3192                             "Unable to get the number of gpus available: %s",
3193                             cudaGetErrorString(cudaGetLastError()));
3194     }
3195 
3196     // as soon as the first successful call to a cuda* function is made, a
3197     // gpu context has been created
3198     g_gpu_context_active = 1;
3199 
3200     if(deviceCount <= 0) {
3201         return PyErr_Format(PyExc_EnvironmentError,
3202                             "Can't use the GPU, no devices support CUDA");
3203     }
3204     if(card_number_provided && (card_nb < 0 || card_nb > (deviceCount - 1))) {
3205         return PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
3206                             "Bad device number %d. Only %d devices available.",
3207                             card_nb,
3208                             deviceCount);
3209     }
3210 
3211     cudaDeviceProp deviceProp;
3212     err = cudaGetDeviceProperties(&deviceProp, card_nb);
3213     if(cudaSuccess != err) {
3214         return PyErr_Format(PyExc_EnvironmentError,
3215                             "Unable to get properties of gpu %i: %s",
3216                             card_nb,
3217                             cudaGetErrorString(cudaGetLastError()));
3218     }
3219 
3220     if(deviceProp.major == 9999 && deviceProp.minor == 9999 ){
3221         return PyErr_Format(PyExc_EnvironmentError,
3222                             "There is no device that supports CUDA");
3223     }
3224 
3225     if(card_number_provided) {
3226         err = cudaSetDevice(card_nb);
3227         if(cudaSuccess != err) {
3228             return PyErr_Format(PyExc_EnvironmentError,
3229                                 "Unable to set device %i: %s",
3230                                 card_nb,
3231                                 cudaGetErrorString(cudaGetLastError()));
3232         }
3233         if (cublas_init() == -1)
3234             return NULL;
3235     }
3236     if(card_number_provided && g_use_cnmem) {
3237         size_t mem = 0;
3238         if (cnmem > 1)
3239             mem = cnmem * 1024 * 1024;
3240         else{
3241             // Clip to 98% to let memory for the driver.
3242             // 98.5% didn't worked in some cases.
3243             if (cnmem > .98){
3244                 cnmem = .98;
3245             }
3246             size_t free = 0, total = 0;
3247             cudaError_t err = cudaMemGetInfo(&free, &total);
3248             if (err != cudaSuccess){
3249                 // Clear the error flag, cudaMemGetInfo doesn't do it.
3250                 // Currently this returns the same thing as err, but if in future
3251                 // it returns something else I still don't see why we should ignore
3252                 // it.  All we want to do here is reset the flag.
3253                 cudaGetLastError();
3254                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
3255                              "Error while getting memory info about the gpu: %s",
3256                              cudaGetErrorString(err));
3257                 return NULL;
3258             }
3259             mem = total * cnmem;
3260         }
3261         if(initCnmem(card_number_provided, card_nb, mem) == -1){
3262             return NULL;
3263         }
3264     }
3265 
3266     Py_INCREF(Py_None);
3267     return Py_None;
3268 }

3317 PyObject *
3318 CudaNdarray_from_gpu_pointer(PyObject* _unused, PyObject* args)
3319 {
3320     int verbose = 0;
3321     PyObject *gpu_ptr = NULL;
3322     PyObject *shapes = NULL;
3323     PyObject *strides = NULL;
3324     PyObject *base = NULL;
3325     PyObject *rval = NULL;
3326 
3327     //args should consist of 3 python objects
3328     //The first is the gpu ptr
3329     //The second if the shape
3330     //The third if the strides
3331     if (! PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "OOOO", &gpu_ptr, &shapes, &strides, &base))
3332         return NULL;
3333 
3334     if (verbose) printf("In CudaNdarray_from_gpu_pointer\n");
3335     if (!PyLong_Check(gpu_ptr))
3336     {
3337         PyErr_Format(PyExc_Exception, "CudaNdarray_from_gpu_pointer: The gpu pointor is not an long");
3338         return NULL;
3339     }
3340 
3341     Py_ssize_t nd =  PyObject_Length(shapes);
3342     if (nd < 0)
3343     {
3344         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "CudaNdarray_from_gpu_pointer: Couldn't get length of second argument");
3345         return NULL;
3346     }
3347     Py_ssize_t nd_stride =  PyObject_Length(strides);
3348     if (nd_stride < 0)
3349     {
3350         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "CudaNdarray_from_gpu_pointer: Couldn't get length of third argument");
3351         return NULL;
3352     }
3353 
3354     if (nd != nd_stride)
3355     {
3356         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "CudaNdarray_from_gpu_pointer: We need the same number of shapes and strides");
3357         return NULL;
3358     }
3359 
3360     rval = CudaNdarray_New();
3361 
3362     if (CudaNdarray_set_nd((CudaNdarray *)rval, nd))
3363     {
3364         //CudaNdarray_set_nd set the error msg
3365         return NULL;
3366     }
3367 
3368     // set gpu pointeur
3369     assert(((CudaNdarray *)rval)->data_allocated == 0);
3370 	float *devptr = (float *)PyInt_AsUnsignedLongLongMask(gpu_ptr);
3371 	if (PyErr_Occurred())
3372 		PyErr_Print();
3373     if (CudaNdarray_set_device_data((CudaNdarray *)rval, devptr, base))
3374     {
3375         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "CudaNdarray_from_gpu_pointer: Error while setting the gpu pointor");
3376         return NULL;
3377     }
3378 	
3379     // Set dims and strides
3380     for (int i = nd-1; i >= 0; --i)
3381     {
3382         PyObject * idx = PyLong_FromLong(i);
3383         if (idx == NULL)
3384         {
3385             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_Exception, "CudaNdarray_from_gpu_pointer: Couldn't make long object to loop over list/tuple");
3386             return NULL;
3387         }
3388         PyObject* dim_ = PyObject_GetItem(shapes, idx);
3389         PyObject* strd_ = PyObject_GetItem(strides, idx);
3390         if (!PyInt_Check(dim_))

3392             PyErr_Format(PyExc_Exception, "CudaNdarray_from_gpu_pointer: shapes[%d] is not an int", i);
3393             return NULL;

3397             PyErr_Format(PyExc_Exception, "CudaNdarray_from_gpu_pointer: strides[%d] is not an int", i);
3398             return NULL;
3399         }
3400         int dim = PyInt_AsLong(dim_);
3401         int strd = PyInt_AsLong(strd_);
3402         CudaNdarray_set_stride((CudaNdarray *)rval, i, strd);
3403         CudaNdarray_set_dim((CudaNdarray *)rval, i, dim);
3404         Py_DECREF(idx);
3405         Py_DECREF(dim_);
3406         Py_DECREF(strd_);
3407     }
3408 
3409     if (verbose) printf("CudaNdarray_from_gpu_pointer normal return\n");
3410     return rval;

3413 PyObject *
3414 CudaNdarray_Dot(PyObject* _unused, PyObject* args)
3415 {
3416     PyObject *l=NULL;
3417     PyObject *r=NULL;
3418     PyObject * rval = NULL;
3419 
3420     //args should consist of two python objects ("OO")
3421     if (! PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "OO", &l, &r))
3422         return NULL;
3423 
3424     if (!CudaNdarray_Check(l) || !CudaNdarray_Check(r))
3425     {
3426         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "CudaNdarray arguments required ");
3427         goto CudaNdarray_dot_fail;
3428     }
3429     if (((CudaNdarray*)l)->nd != 2)
3430     {
3431         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "need 2d CudaNdarray arg for now");
3432         goto CudaNdarray_dot_fail;
3433     }
3434     if (((CudaNdarray*)r)->nd != 2)
3435     {
3436         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "need 2d CudaNdarray arg for now");
3437         goto CudaNdarray_dot_fail;
3438     }
3439     rval = CudaNdarray_New();
3440     if (!rval)
3441     {
3442         goto CudaNdarray_dot_fail;
3443     }
3444     int dims[2];
3445     dims[0] = CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS((CudaNdarray*)l)[0];
3446     dims[1] = CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS((CudaNdarray*)r)[1];
3447     if (CudaNdarray_alloc_contiguous((CudaNdarray*)rval, 2, dims))
3448     {
3449         goto CudaNdarray_dot_fail;
3450     }
3451     if (CudaNdarray_gemm(1.0, (CudaNdarray*)l, (CudaNdarray*)r, 0.0, (CudaNdarray*)rval))
3452     {
3453         goto CudaNdarray_dot_fail;
3454     }
3455 
3456     return rval;
3457 
3458     CudaNdarray_dot_fail:
3459     Py_XDECREF(rval);
3460     return NULL;
3461 }

3465 {
3466     /*
3467      * TODO: DOC what this function should do in the various cases of
3468      * What is 'strict' supposed to mean in the context of this function?
3469      * What do we do with input that could be interpreted as matching the broadcastable pattern in strict vs. non-strict cases?
3470      *
3471      */
3472     PyObject *py_data=NULL;
3473     PyArrayObject * data = NULL;
3474     int strict = 0;
3475     PyObject * broadcastable=NULL;
3476     PyObject * storage=NULL;
3477     CudaNdarray * rval=NULL;
3478 
3479     //Python object references which are provided to the caller are borrowed references
3480     if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "OOiO", &py_data, &broadcastable, &strict, &storage)) return NULL;
3481 
3482     if (!PyTuple_Check(broadcastable)){
3483         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "broadcastable arg should be a tuple of int.");
3484         return NULL;
3485     }
3486     Py_INCREF(py_data);
3487     Py_INCREF(broadcastable);
3488 
3489     CudaNdarray * cnda = (CudaNdarray*)py_data;
3490 
3491     if (strict || CudaNdarray_Check(py_data))
3492     {
3493         //TODO: support non-strict "casting" from a vt to the broadcastable/type/size that we need.
3494         if (!CudaNdarray_Check(py_data))
3495         {
3496             Py_DECREF(py_data);
3497             Py_DECREF(broadcastable);
3498             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "strict mode requires CudaNdarray");
3499             return NULL;
3500         }
3501         if (cnda->nd != PyTuple_Size(broadcastable))
3502         {
3503             Py_DECREF(py_data);
3504             Py_DECREF(broadcastable);
3505             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "Wrong rank: %i vs %li", cnda->nd, (long)PyTuple_Size(broadcastable));
3506             return NULL;
3507         }
3508         for (int i = 0; i < cnda->nd; ++i)
3509         {
3510             if ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(cnda)[i] > 1) && PyInt_AsLong(PyTuple_GetItem(broadcastable, Py_ssize_t(i))))
3511             {
3512                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "Non-unit size in broadcastable vt dimension %i", i);
3513                 Py_DECREF(py_data);
3514                 Py_DECREF(broadcastable);
3515                 return NULL;
3516             }else if (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(cnda)[i] == 1 && CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(cnda)[i] != 0){
3517                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "Non-zeros strides(%d) on dimension %d of size 1",
3518                              CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(cnda)[i], i);
3519                 Py_DECREF(py_data);
3520                 Py_DECREF(broadcastable);
3521                 return NULL;
3522             }
3523         }
3524         Py_DECREF(broadcastable);
3525         return py_data;
3526     }
3527     else
3528     {
3529         data = (PyArrayObject*)PyArray_FromObject(py_data, REAL_TYPENUM, PyTuple_Size(broadcastable), PyTuple_Size(broadcastable));
3530         if (!data)
3531         {
3532             //err message already defined
3533             Py_DECREF(py_data);
3534             Py_DECREF(broadcastable);
3535             return NULL;
3536         }
3537         for (int i = 0; i < PyArray_NDIM(data); ++i)
3538         {
3539             if ((PyArray_DIMS(data)[i] > 1) && PyInt_AsLong(PyTuple_GetItem(broadcastable, Py_ssize_t(i))))
3540             {
3541                 PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "Non-unit size in broadcastable dimension %i", i);
3542                 Py_DECREF(data);
3543                 Py_DECREF(py_data);
3544                 Py_DECREF(broadcastable);
3545                 return NULL;
3546             }
3547         }
3548         if (storage && CudaNdarray_Check(storage))
3549         {
3550             rval = (CudaNdarray*) storage;
3551             Py_INCREF(rval);
3552         }
3553         else
3554         {
3555             rval = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_New();
3556         }
3557         if (rval)
3558         {
3559             if (CudaNdarray_CopyFromArray(rval, data))
3560             {
3561                 Py_DECREF(rval);
3562                 rval = NULL;
3563             }
3564         }
3565         Py_DECREF(data);
3566         Py_DECREF(py_data);
3567         Py_DECREF(broadcastable);
3568         return (PyObject*)rval;
3569     }
3570 }

3727 static int
3728 cublas_init()
3729 {
3730 	printf("Theano: Initializing cuBLAS\n");
3731 
3732     cublasStatus_t err;
3733     err = cublasCreate(&handle);
3734     if (CUBLAS_STATUS_SUCCESS != err)
3735     {
3736         if(CUBLAS_STATUS_NOT_INITIALIZED == err)
3737             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError,
3738                             "cublasCreate() returned this error "
3739                             "'the CUDA Runtime initialization failed'");
3740         else if(CUBLAS_STATUS_ALLOC_FAILED == err)
3741             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError,
3742                             "cublasCreate() returned this error "
3743                             "'the resources could not be allocated'");
3744         else
3745             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError,
3746                             "unknow error during returned by cublasCreate()");
3747         return -1;
3748     }
3749     // Set the default stream as the one to execute on (default)
3750     cublasSetStream(handle, NULL);
3751     // Pointer to scalars are on the host (also default)
3752     cublasSetPointerMode(handle, CUBLAS_POINTER_MODE_HOST);
3753 #if CUDA_VERSION >= 5000
3754     // atomics can be used in kernels to speed up operations (not default)
3755     // This may lead to a slight variance from run to run in some operations
3756     cublasSetAtomicsMode(handle, CUBLAS_ATOMICS_ALLOWED);
3757 #endif
3758     return 0;
3759 }

3765     if (handle != NULL)

3767     // No point in handling any errors here
3768     handle = NULL;

3771 int
3772 CudaNdarray_CopyFromArray(CudaNdarray * self, PyArrayObject*obj)
3773 {
3774     int err = CudaNdarray_alloc_contiguous(self, PyArray_NDIM(obj),
3775                                            PyArray_DIMS(obj));
3776     if (err) {
3777         return err;
3778     }
3779 
3780     int typenum = PyArray_TYPE(obj);
3781     if (typenum != REAL_TYPENUM)
3782     {
3783         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "can only copy from float arrays");
3784         return -1;
3785     }
3786     assert( 4 ==  PyArray_ITEMSIZE(obj));
3787     PyArrayObject * py_src = (PyArrayObject *)PyArray_ContiguousFromAny(
3788         (PyObject*)obj, typenum, self->nd, self->nd);
3789     if (!py_src) {
3790         return -1;
3791     }
3792     npy_intp py_src_size = PyArray_SIZE(py_src);
3793     void *py_src_data = PyArray_DATA(py_src);
3794     cudaError_t cerr;
3795     CNDA_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS;
3796     cerr = cudaMemcpy(self->devdata, py_src_data,
3797                       py_src_size * sizeof(real),
3798                       cudaMemcpyHostToDevice);
3799     //CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;  // unneeded because cudaMemcpy is blocking anyway
3800     CNDA_END_ALLOW_THREADS;
3801     if (cudaSuccess != cerr)
3802     {
3803         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
3804                      "Cuda error '%s' while copying %lli data element"
3805                      " to device memory",
3806                      cudaGetErrorString(cerr),
3807                      (long long)py_src_size);
3808         Py_DECREF(py_src);
3809         return -1;
3810     }
3811     Py_DECREF(py_src);
3812     return 0;
3813 }

3828 /**
3829  * Initialize 'self' as a view of 'base', with memory storage 'data'
3830  */
3831 
3832 int CudaNdarray_set_device_data(CudaNdarray * self, float * data, PyObject * base)
3833 {
3834     if (self->data_allocated)
3835     {
3836         assert(self->devdata);
3837         if (device_free(self->devdata))
3838         {
3839             self->devdata = NULL;
3840             self->data_allocated = 0;
3841             return -1;
3842         }
3843     }
3844     // Get the original base object (base.base.base...)
3845     PyObject * orig_base = base;
3846     // base is not always a CudaNdarray. It can be a GpuArray from pycuda, ...
3847     while (orig_base && CudaNdarray_Check(orig_base) && ((CudaNdarray*) orig_base)->base)
3848     {
3849         // base_base is itself a view
3850         orig_base = ((CudaNdarray*) orig_base)->base;
3851     }
3852     //N.B. XDECREF and XINCREF are no-ops for NULL pointers
3853     if (self->base != orig_base)
3854     {
3855         Py_XDECREF(self->base);
3856         self->base = orig_base;
3857         Py_XINCREF(self->base);
3858     }
3859     self->data_allocated = 0;
3860     self->devdata = data;
3861     return 0;
3862 }

3864 static __global__ void k_copy_1d(const int N, const float * x, const int sx, float * y, const int sy)
3865 {
3866     for (int i = threadIdx.x + blockIdx.x * blockDim.x; i < N; i += gridDim.x*blockDim.x)
3867     {
3868         y[i*sy] = x[i*sx];
3869     }
3870 }
3871 
3872 // N1 through N4 are the size of y
3873 static __global__ void k_copy_4d(const int N1,
3874         const int N2, const int N3, const int N4,
3875         const float * x, const int sx1, const int sx2, const int sx3,
3876         const int sx4,  float * y, const int sy1, const int sy2,
3877         const int sy3, const int sy4)
3878 {
3879     // These must be made int instead of unsigned int due to a bug in nvcc
3880     int bx = blockIdx.x;
3881     int by = blockIdx.y;
3882 
3883     for (int i = bx; i < N1; i += gridDim.x)
3884     {
3885         for (int j = by; j < N2; j += gridDim.y)
3886         {
3887             for (int k = threadIdx.x; k < N3; k += (int) blockDim.x)
3888             {
3889                 for (int l = threadIdx.y; l < N4; l += (int) blockDim.y)
3890                 {
3891                     y[i * sy1 + j * sy2 + k * sy3 + l * sy4] =
3892                         x[i * sx1 + j * sx2 + k * sx3 + l * sx4];
3893                 }
3894             }
3895         }
3896     }
3897 }

3899 //copy from other into self
3900 int CudaNdarray_CopyFromCudaNdarray(CudaNdarray * self,
3901                                     const CudaNdarray * other,
3902                                     bool unbroadcast)
3903 {
3904     int verbose = 0;
3905     if (verbose>1) fprintf(stderr, "CudaNdarray_CopyFromCudaNdarray\n");
3906 
3907     //standard elemwise size checks
3908     if (self->nd == -1)
3909     {
3910         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError,
3911                         "can't copy into un-initialized CudaNdarray");
3912         return -1;
3913     }
3914     CudaNdarray * new_other = NULL;
3915 
3916     if (self->nd < other->nd)
3917     {
3918         PyErr_Format(PyExc_NotImplementedError,
3919             "CudaNdarray_CopyFromCudaNdarray: The number of dimensions of the "
3920             "destination needs to be >= the number of dimensions of the "
3921             "source. Got %d and %d.", self->nd, other->nd);
3922         return -1;
3923     }
3924     else if (self->nd != other->nd)
3925     {
3926         new_other = (CudaNdarray *) CudaNdarray_View(other);
3927         int added_dims = self->nd - other->nd;
3928         int* pattern = (int*) alloca(self->nd * sizeof(int));
3929         for(int i = 0; i < added_dims; i++)
3930             pattern[i] = -1;
3931         for(int i = 0; i < other->nd; i++)
3932             pattern[i + added_dims] = i;
3933         CudaNdarray_dimshuffle(new_other, self->nd, pattern);
3934         other = new_other;
3935     }
3936     assert(self->nd == other->nd);
3937     //standard elemwise dim checks (also compute total size)
3938     unsigned int size = 1;
3939     unsigned int size_source = 1;
3940     for (int i = 0; i< self->nd; ++i)
3941     {
3942         if ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i] != CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(other)[i])
3943             && (1!=CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(other)[i] || !unbroadcast) )
3944         {
3945           PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
3946                        "CudaNdarray_CopyFromCudaNdarray:"
3947                        " need same dimensions for dim %d,"
3948                        " destination=%d, source=%d",
3949                        i, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i],
3950                        CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(other)[i]);
3951           Py_XDECREF(new_other);
3952           return -1;
3953         }
3954         size *= (unsigned int) CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i];
3955         size_source *= (unsigned int) CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(other)[i];
3956     }
3957     if (0 == size)
3958     {
3959         Py_XDECREF(new_other);
3960         return 0; //nothing to copy, we're done.
3961     }
3962     if (CudaNdarray_is_c_contiguous(self) &&
3963         CudaNdarray_is_c_contiguous(other) &&
3964         size == size_source)
3965     {
3966         if (verbose)
3967             fprintf(stderr, "Copying contiguous vector with cublasScopy\n");
3968 
3969         cublasStatus_t err;
3970         err = cublasScopy(handle, size, CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(other), 1,
3971                           CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self), 1);
3972         CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
3973         Py_XDECREF(new_other);
3974         if (CUBLAS_STATUS_SUCCESS != err)
3975         {
3976             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "Error copying memory");
3977             return -1;
3978         }
3979         return 0;
3980     }
3981     //TODO: rewrite these copy operations to be more efficient
3982     //      See, for example the transpose example in the cuda_sdk.
3983     switch (self->nd)
3984     {
3985         case 0: // scalar
3986             {
3987                 // THIS CASE SHOULD NEVER HAPPEN BECAUSE SCALARS ARE ALWAYS C CONTIGUOUS
3988                 assert(0);
3989             }; break;
3990         case 1: // vector
3991             {
3992                 if (verbose) fprintf(stderr, "Copying non-contiguous vector\n");
3993                 if (verbose) fprint_CudaNdarray(stderr, other);
3994                 unsigned int n_blocks = std::min(size,
3995                                                  (unsigned int)NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS);
3996                 unsigned int n_threads = std::min(ceil_intdiv(size, n_blocks),
3997                                                   (unsigned int)NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK);
3998                 k_copy_1d<<<n_blocks, n_threads>>>(size,
3999                                             CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(other),
4000                                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(other)[0],
4001                                             CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
4002                                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0]);
4003                 CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
4004                 cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
4005                 if( cudaSuccess != err)
4006                 {
4007                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
4008                                  "Cuda error: %s: %s. (n_blocks=%i,"
4009                                  " n_threads_per_block=%i)\n", "k_copy_1d",
4010                                  cudaGetErrorString(err), n_blocks, n_threads);
4011                     Py_XDECREF(new_other);
4012                     return -1;
4013                 }
4014             }; break;
4015         case 4: // 4-tensor
4016             {
4017                 if (verbose)
4018                 {
4019                     if (0 != fprint_CudaNdarray(stderr, other))
4020                     {
4021                         Py_XDECREF(new_other);
4022                         return -1;
4023                     }
4024                 }
4025 
4026                 // The blocks implement the looping over the first two axes so
4027                 // this needs to be (N1, N2)
4028                 dim3 n_blocks( std::min(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0],
4029                                         NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS),
4030                                std::min(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[1],
4031                                         NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS));
4032                 // For the threads, just make as many as possible
4033                 dim3 n_threads( std::min( (unsigned int) CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[2],
4034                                  (unsigned int) NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK),
4035                                 std::min( (unsigned int) CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[3],
4036                                     (unsigned int) NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK));
4037 
4038                 n_threads.x = std::min( (unsigned int) 32, (unsigned int) n_threads.x);
4039                 n_threads.y = std::min( n_threads.y, NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK / n_threads.x);
4040 
4041                 k_copy_4d<<<n_blocks, n_threads>>>(
4042                                             // size of y
4043                                             (unsigned int) CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0], // N1
4044                                             (unsigned int) CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[1], // N2
4045                                             (unsigned int) CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[2], // N3
4046                                             (unsigned int) CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[3], // N4
4047                                             CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(other), // x
4048                                             // x strides
4049                                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(other)[0],
4050                                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(other)[1],
4051                                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(other)[2],
4052                                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(other)[3],
4053                                             CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self), // y
4054                                             // y strides
4055                                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[0],
4056                                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[1],
4057                                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[2],
4058                                             CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[3]
4059                                             );
4060                 CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
4061                 cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
4062                 if( cudaSuccess != err)
4063                 {
4064                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
4065                                  "Cuda error: %s: %s.",
4066                                  "k_copy_4d",
4067                                  cudaGetErrorString(err));
4068                     Py_XDECREF(new_other);
4069                     return -1;
4070                 }
4071             }; break;
4072         default:
4073             {
4074                 assert (cudaSuccess == cudaGetLastError());
4075                 if (verbose)
4076                     fprintf(stderr,
4077                             "Copying with default version unbroadcast=%d\n",
4078                             unbroadcast);
4079                 // call worker routine
4080                 unsigned int threads_per_block = std::min(size,
4081                                                           (unsigned int)NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK);
4082                 unsigned int n_blocks = std::min(ceil_intdiv(size, threads_per_block),
4083                                                  (unsigned int)NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS);
4084                 const CudaNdarray * cuda_dims = other;
4085                 if(unbroadcast)
4086                     cuda_dims = self;
4087                 //copy from other into self
4088                 k_elemwise_unary_rowmajor_copy<<<n_blocks, threads_per_block>>>(
4089                         size,
4090                         (unsigned int)other->nd,
4091                         (const int *)CudaNdarray_DEV_DIMS(cuda_dims),
4092                         (const float*)CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(other),
4093                         (const int *)CudaNdarray_DEV_STRIDES(other),
4094                         CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
4095                         (const int *)CudaNdarray_DEV_STRIDES(self));
4096                 CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
4097                 cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
4098                 if(verbose>1)
4099                     fprintf(stderr,
4100                             "INFO k_elemwise_unary_rowmaj (n_blocks=%i,"
4101                             " n_threads_per_block=%i)\n",
4102                             n_blocks, threads_per_block);
4103                 if( cudaSuccess != err)
4104                 {
4105                     //fprint_CudaNdarray(stderr, self);
4106                     //fprint_CudaNdarray(stderr, other);
4107                     PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
4108                                  "Cuda error: %s: %s. (n_blocks=%i,"
4109                                  " n_threads_per_block=%i)\n",
4110                                  "k_elemwise_unary_rowmajor_copy",
4111                                  cudaGetErrorString(err), n_blocks,
4112                                  threads_per_block);
4113                     Py_XDECREF(new_other);
4114                     return -1;
4115                 }
4116             }
4117     };
4118     Py_XDECREF(new_other);
4119     return 0;
4120 }
4121 
4122 int CudaNdarray_gemm(float alpha, const CudaNdarray * A, const CudaNdarray * B, float beta, CudaNdarray * C)
4123 {
4124     if (A->nd != 2)
4125     {
4126         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "non-matrix arg A to gemm");
4127         return -1;
4128     }
4129     if (B->nd != 2)
4130     {
4131         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "non-matrix arg B to gemm");
4132         return -1;
4133     }
4134     if (C->nd != 2)
4135     {
4136         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "non-matrix arg C to gemm");
4137         return -1;
4138     }
4139 
4140     // We must allow dimensions to be zeros.
4141     if ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1] != CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[0])
4142             || (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0] != CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0])
4143             || (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[1] != CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1]))
4144     {
4145         PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "dimension mismatch in args to gemm (%i,%i)x(%i,%i)->(%i,%i)",
4146                 CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0],
4147                 CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1],
4148                 CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[0],
4149                 CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[1],
4150                 CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0],
4151                 CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1]);
4152         return -1;
4153     }
4154 
4155     // If matrix A or B has non-unit size and non-unit stride in both
4156     // dimensions, we can make a copy.
4157     CudaNdarray * A_new = NULL;
4158     CudaNdarray * B_new = NULL;
4159     if (((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0] > 1)
4160          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] != 1)
4161          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1] > 1)
4162          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] != 1))
4163         || (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] < 0)
4164         || (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] < 0))
4165     {
4166         A_new = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_Copy(A);
4167         if (!A_new)
4168             return -1;
4169         A = A_new;
4170     }
4171 
4172     if (((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[0] > 1)
4173          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(B)[0] != 1)
4174          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[1] > 1)
4175          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(B)[1] != 1))
4176         || (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(B)[0] < 0)
4177         || (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(B)[1] < 0))
4178     {
4179         B_new = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_Copy(B);
4180         if (!B_new)
4181         {
4182             // If A_new is NULL, meaning A was not copied nothing happens
4183             Py_XDECREF(A_new);
4184             return -1;
4185         }
4186         B = B_new;
4187     }
4188 
4189     // If matrix C has non-unit size and non-unit stride in both
4190     // dimensions, or negative strides, we can't operate. We cannot copy
4191     // C either, because the calling code will expect the result to be
4192     // in the original C container.
4193     if (((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0] > 1)
4194          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[0] != 1)
4195          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1] > 1)
4196          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[1] != 1))
4197         || (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[0] < 0)
4198         || (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[1] < 0))
4199     {
4200         PyErr_Format(PyExc_AssertionError,
4201                      "non-unit or negative stride in gemm arg C (%i,%i) of shape (%i,%i)",
4202                      CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[0],
4203                      CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[1],
4204                      CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0],
4205                      CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1]);
4206         Py_XDECREF(A_new);
4207         Py_XDECREF(B_new);
4208         return -1;
4209     }
4210 
4211     // the unit integer is divided logically into three fields of 4 bits
4212     // the lowermost 4 bits encode the stride pattern of the output
4213     // the next higher 4 bits encode the B variable (or y)
4214     // the next higher 4 bits encode the C variable (or x)
4215     //
4216     // the stride pattern for each input is encoded as 0 for unit stride from col to col (Row major)
4217     //                                                 1 for unit stride from row to row (Col major)
4218 
4219     // a stride of 0 implies a dimension of 1 - so we can actually define
4220     // a stride of 0 as a 'unit' stride because gemm will never use it.
4221     // If a dimension is 0, its stride will not be used either, so we can
4222     // consider it a 'unit' stride too.
4223     int unit = 0;
4224     if (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] == 1 || CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1] <= 1) {
4225         unit |= (0x0 << 8);
4226     } else if (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] == 1 || CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0] <= 1) {
4227         unit |= (0x1 << 8);
4228     } else {
4229         unit |= (0x2 << 8);
4230     }
4231     if (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(B)[1] == 1 || CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[1] <= 1) {
4232         unit |= (0x0 << 4);
4233     } else if (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(B)[0] == 1 || CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[0] <= 1) {
4234         unit |= (0x1 << 4);
4235     } else {
4236         unit |= (0x2 << 4);
4237     }
4238     if (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[1] == 1 || CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1] <= 1) {
4239         unit |= (0x0 << 0);
4240     } else if (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[0] == 1 || CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0] <= 1) {
4241         unit |= (0x1 << 0);
4242     } else {
4243         unit |= (0x2 << 0);
4244     }
4245 
4246     /* create appropriate strides for malformed matrices that are row or column
4247      * vectors
4248      */
4249     int sa_0 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] : CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1];
4250     int sa_1 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] : CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0];
4251     int sb_0 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[0] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(B)[0] : CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[1];
4252     int sb_1 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[1] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(B)[1] : CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[0];
4253     int sc_0 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[0] : CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1];
4254     int sc_1 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[1] : CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0];
4255 
4256     float* a = CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(A);
4257     float* b = CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(B);
4258     float* c = CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(C);
4259     cublasOperation_t N = CUBLAS_OP_N;
4260     cublasOperation_t T = CUBLAS_OP_T;
4261     //std::cerr << (unit/256) MOD 16 << (unit / 16) MOD 16 << unit MOD 16<< '\\n';
4262     // There should be no negative stride at that point
4263 #define CHK_STRIDE_SGEMM(T0, T1, D0, D1, D2, a, x, sx, y, sy, b, z, sz) \
4264     if (sx == 0){sx = 1;}\
4265     if (sy == 0){sy = 1;}\
4266     if (sz == 0){sz = 1;}\
4267     if ((sx > 0) && (sy > 0) && (sz > 0)) { \
4268         err = cublasSgemm(handle, T0, T1, D0, D1, D2, &a, x, sx, y, sy, &b, z, sz); \
4269     } else { \
4270         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_AssertionError, "negative stride to sGemm");\
4271         Py_XDECREF(A_new);\
4272         Py_XDECREF(B_new);\
4273         return -1; \
4274     }
4275 
4276     cublasStatus_t err;
4277     switch(unit)
4278     {
4279         case 0x000: CHK_STRIDE_SGEMM(N, N, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1], alpha, b, sb_0, a, sa_0, beta, c, sc_0); break;
4280         case 0x100: CHK_STRIDE_SGEMM(N, T, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1], alpha, b, sb_0, a, sa_1, beta, c, sc_0); break;
4281         case 0x010: CHK_STRIDE_SGEMM(T, N, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1], alpha, b, sb_1, a, sa_0, beta, c, sc_0); break;
4282         case 0x110: CHK_STRIDE_SGEMM(T, T, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1], alpha, b, sb_1, a, sa_1, beta, c, sc_0); break;
4283         case 0x001: CHK_STRIDE_SGEMM(T, T, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1], alpha, a, sa_0, b, sb_0, beta, c, sc_1); break;
4284         case 0x101: CHK_STRIDE_SGEMM(N, T, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1], alpha, a, sa_1, b, sb_0, beta, c, sc_1); break;
4285         case 0x011: CHK_STRIDE_SGEMM(T, N, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1], alpha, a, sa_0, b, sb_1, beta, c, sc_1); break;
4286         case 0x111: CHK_STRIDE_SGEMM(N, N, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1], alpha, a, sa_1, b, sb_1, beta, c, sc_1); break;
4287         default: PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "some matrix has no unit stride (unit=%x)", unit);
4288                  return -1;
4289     };
4290     CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
4291     Py_XDECREF(A_new);
4292     Py_XDECREF(B_new);
4293 
4294     if (CUBLAS_STATUS_SUCCESS != err)
4295     {
4296         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
4297                      "cublasSgemm failed (%i) %s\n"
4298                      " unit=%x N=%d, c.dims=[%d %d], a.dim=[%d %d], alpha=%f, beta=%f, a=%p, b=%p, c=%p"
4299                      " sa_0=%d, sa_1=%d, sb_0=%d, sb_1=%d, sc_0=%d, sc_1=%d",
4300                      err,  cublasGetErrorString(err),
4301                      unit, N,
4302                      CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0],
4303                      CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[1],
4304                      CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1],
4305                      alpha, beta, a, b, c, sa_0, sa_1, sb_0, sb_1, sc_0, sc_1);
4306 
4307         return -1;
4308     }
4309     return 0;
4310 }
4311 
4312 int CudaNdarray_sgemv(float alpha, const CudaNdarray * A, const CudaNdarray * B, float beta, CudaNdarray * C)
4313 {
4314     /**
4315     * C <- alpha A B + beta C
4316     *    A : matrix
4317     *    B, C: vector
4318     *    alpha, beta: scalars
4319     */
4320     if (A->nd != 2) { PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "non-matrix arg to gemv"); return -1; }
4321     if (B->nd != 1) { PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "non-vector arg to gemv"); return -1; }
4322     if (C->nd != 1) { PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "non-vector arg to gemv"); return -1; }
4323 
4324     // We must allow dimensions to be zeros.
4325     if ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1] != CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[0])
4326             || (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0] != CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0]))
4327     {
4328         PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "dimension mismatch in args to gemv (%i,%i)x(%i)->(%i)",
4329                 CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0],
4330                 CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1],
4331                 CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[0],
4332                 CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0]);
4333         return -1;
4334     }
4335 
4336     // If matrix A has non-unit size and non-unit stride in both
4337     // dimensions, or negative strides, we cannot operate, but we can
4338     // make a copy.
4339     CudaNdarray * A_new = NULL;
4340     CudaNdarray * B_new = NULL;
4341     if (((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0] > 1)
4342          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] != 1)
4343          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1] > 1)
4344          && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] != 1))
4345         || (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] < 0)
4346         || (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] < 0))
4347     {
4348         A_new = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_Copy(A);
4349         if (!A_new)
4350             return -1;
4351         A = A_new;
4352     }
4353 
4354     // If vector B as a negative stride, we also have to make a copy.
4355     if (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(B)[0] < 0)
4356     {
4357         B_new = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_Copy(B);
4358         if (!B_new)
4359         {
4360             // If A was not copied, A_new is NULL, and Py_XDECREF does not
4361             // do anything
4362             Py_XDECREF(A_new);
4363             return -1;
4364         }
4365         B = B_new;
4366     }
4367 
4368     // cudablas does not handle negative strides as expected
4369     if (   (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] < 0)
4370         || (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] < 0))
4371     {
4372         PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "illegal strides in args to gemv (%i,%i)",
4373                 CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0],
4374                 CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1]);
4375         Py_XDECREF(A_new);
4376         Py_XDECREF(B_new);
4377         return -1;
4378     }
4379 
4380     /* create appropriate strides for malformed matrices that are row or column
4381      * vectors
4382      */
4383     int sa_0 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] : CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1];
4384     int sa_1 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] : CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0];
4385     int sb_0 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[0] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(B)[0] : 1;
4386     int sc_0 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[0] : 1;
4387 
4388     if (sa_0 == 0)
4389         sa_0 = 1;
4390     if (sa_1 == 0)
4391         sa_1 = 1;
4392 
4393     // This is important because we can end up not calling Sgemv at all
4394     cublasStatus_t err = CUBLAS_STATUS_SUCCESS;
4395     if (CudaNdarray_SIZE(C)) {
4396         if ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0] <= 1)
4397             || ((CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] == 1)
4398                 && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] > 0)))
4399         {
4400             err = cublasSgemv(handle, CUBLAS_OP_N,
4401                     CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1],
4402                     &alpha,
4403                     CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(A), sa_1,
4404                     CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(B), sb_0,
4405                     &beta,
4406                     CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(C), sc_0);
4407         }
4408         else if ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1] <= 1)
4409                 || ((CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] == 1)
4410                     && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] > 0)))
4411         {
4412             err = cublasSgemv(handle, CUBLAS_OP_T,
4413                     CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0],
4414                     &alpha,
4415                     CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(A), sa_0,
4416                     CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(B), sb_0,
4417                     &beta,
4418                     CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(C), sc_0);
4419         }
4420         else
4421         {
4422             PyErr_Format(PyExc_AssertionError,
4423                          "Unexpected stride pattern in gemv: (%i, %i) x %i -> %i.\n"
4424                          "Shapes are: (%i, %i) x %i -> %i\n",
4425                          CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0],
4426                          CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1],
4427                          CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(B)[0],
4428                          CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(C)[0],
4429                          CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0],
4430                          CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1],
4431                          CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(B)[0],
4432                          CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(C)[0]);
4433             Py_XDECREF(A_new);
4434             Py_XDECREF(B_new);
4435             return -1;
4436         }
4437     }
4438 
4439     CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
4440     Py_XDECREF(A_new);
4441     Py_XDECREF(B_new);
4442 
4443     if (CUBLAS_STATUS_SUCCESS != err)
4444     {
4445         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
4446                      "cublasSgemv failed (%i)",
4447                      err);
4448         return -1;
4449     }
4450     return 0;
4451 }
4452 
4453 int CudaNdarray_sger(float alpha, const CudaNdarray * x, const CudaNdarray * y, CudaNdarray * A) {
4454     if (x->nd != 1) { PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "non-vector arg x to sger"); return -1; }
4455     if (y->nd != 1) { PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "non-vector arg y to sger"); return -1; }
4456     if (A->nd != 2) { PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "non-matrix arg A to sger"); return -1; }
4457 
4458     if ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0] != CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(x)[0])
4459         || (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1] != CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(y)[0])) {
4460         PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError,
4461                      "dimension mismatch in args to sger (%i)x(%i)->(%i,%i)",
4462                      CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(x)[0],
4463                      CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(y)[0],
4464                      CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0],
4465                      CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1]);
4466         return -1;
4467     }
4468 
4469     int x_strides = CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(x)[0];
4470     CudaNdarray * x_new = NULL;
4471     if(x_strides == 0){
4472         if(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(x)[0] != 1){
4473             PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
4474                          "CudaNdarray_sger: Invalid input x (should not happen)."
4475                          " We received a CudaNdarray vector with a stride of 0"
4476                          " that has more than 1 element!");
4477             return -1;
4478         }
4479         x_strides = 1;
4480     } else if(x_strides < 0){
4481         x_new = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_Copy(x);
4482         x = x_new;
4483         x_strides = CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(x)[0];
4484     }
4485 
4486     int y_strides = CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(y)[0];
4487     CudaNdarray * y_new = NULL;
4488     if(y_strides == 0){
4489         if(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(y)[0] != 1){
4490             PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
4491                          "CudaNdarray_sger: Invalid input y (should not happen)."
4492                          " We received a CudaNdarray vector with a stride of 0"
4493                          " that has more than 1 elements!");
4494             Py_XDECREF(x_new);
4495             return -1;
4496         }
4497         y_strides = 1;
4498     } else if(y_strides < 0){
4499         y_new = (CudaNdarray*) CudaNdarray_Copy(y);
4500         y = y_new;
4501         y_strides = CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(y)[0];
4502     }
4503 
4504     // Create appropriate strides if A is a row or column vector
4505     int sa_0 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0]
4506                                                  : CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1];
4507     int sa_1 = (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1] > 1) ? CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1]
4508                                                  : CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0];
4509 
4510     // This is important because we can end up not calling Sger at all
4511     cublasStatus_t err = CUBLAS_STATUS_SUCCESS;
4512     if(CudaNdarray_SIZE(A)){
4513         // If A is in col-major
4514         if ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0] <= 1)
4515             || ((CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] == 1)
4516                 && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] > 0)))
4517         {
4518             err = cublasSger(handle, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(x)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(y)[0], &alpha,
4519                        CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(x), x_strides,
4520                        CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(y), y_strides,
4521                        CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(A), sa_1);
4522         }
4523         // Since Sger expects A in col-major, we invert x and y to fake this.
4524         else if ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1] <= 1)
4525                 || ((CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1] == 1)
4526                     && (CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0] > 0)))
4527         {
4528             err = cublasSger(handle, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(y)[0], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(x)[0], &alpha,
4529                        CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(y), y_strides,
4530                        CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(x), x_strides,
4531                        CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(A), sa_0);
4532         }
4533         // A has to be either c- or f-contiguous, with no negative strides
4534         else
4535         {
4536             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_NotImplementedError,
4537                             "non-contiguous A, or negative strides, in sger");
4538             Py_XDECREF(x_new);
4539             Py_XDECREF(y_new);
4540             return -1;
4541         }
4542     }
4543     CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
4544     Py_XDECREF(x_new);
4545     Py_XDECREF(y_new);
4546 
4547     if (CUBLAS_STATUS_SUCCESS != err)
4548     {
4549         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError,
4550                      "cublasSger failed (%i)",
4551                      err);
4552         return -1;
4553     }
4554 
4555     return 0;
4556 }
