4558 /**
4559  *
4560  * Precondition:
4561  *  a->dim[d] == (dims_a[d]==0) ? (1 << log2_dims_a[d]) : dims_a[d]
4562  *  z->dim[d] == (z_str[d]==0) ? 1 : dims_a[d];
4563  *
4564  *  TODO: templatize this function to support other reductions.
4565  *  All that needs to change is the initial value for sum, and the reduction operator.
4566  */
4567 
4568 static __global__ void kernel_reduce_sum(const unsigned int size_z,
4569         const unsigned int nd,
4570         const int * dims_a,
4571         const int * log2_dims_a,
4572         const int * a_str,
4573         const float * a_data,
4574         const int * z_str,
4575         float * z_data)
4576 {
4577     const unsigned int idx = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
4578     const unsigned int numThreads = blockDim.x * gridDim.x;
4579 
4580     //structure data contains the strides and dimensions of both a and z
4581     // a_dim[0], a_dim[1], ... a_dim[nd-1],
4582     // a_log2dim[0], a_log2dim[1], ... a_log2dim[nd-1],
4583     // a_str[0], ... a_str[nd-1],
4584     // z_str[0], ... z_str[nd-1]
4585     extern __shared__ int structure_data[];
4586     for (unsigned int i = threadIdx.x; i < nd; i += blockDim.x)
4587     {
4588         structure_data[i+0*nd] = dims_a[i];
4589         structure_data[i+1*nd] = log2_dims_a[i];
4590         structure_data[i+2*nd] = a_str[i];
4591         structure_data[i+3*nd] = z_str[i];
4592     }
4593     dims_a = structure_data;
4594     log2_dims_a = structure_data + nd;
4595     a_str = structure_data + 2*nd;
4596     z_str = structure_data + 3*nd;
4597 
4598     __syncthreads(); //wait for all the shared structure to be loaded
4599 
4600     for (unsigned int i = idx; i < size_z; i += numThreads)
4601     {
4602         unsigned int ii = i;
4603         const float * a_data_i = a_data;
4604         float * z_data_i = z_data;
4605         unsigned int n_reduce_elements = 1;
4606         unsigned int n_reduce_dims = 0;
4607         unsigned int reduce_dim0 = nd-1;
4608 
4609 
4610         //In this loop, we locate the initial element of the slice that we'd like to reduce with this thread
4611         //  At the same time, we [re]calculate the size of that slice (n_reduce_elements)
4612         for (unsigned int d = 0; d < nd; ++d)
4613         {
4614             if (a_str[d] && (!z_str[d])) // this means 'd' is a dimension we are reducing over
4615             {
4616                 n_reduce_elements *= dims_a[d];
4617                 n_reduce_dims += 1;
4618                 reduce_dim0 = (d < reduce_dim0) ? d : reduce_dim0;
4619             }
4620             else //'d' is not a dimension that we are reducing over
4621             {
4622                 unsigned int pos_d;
4623                 if (log2_dims_a[d]==-1) //TODO: when things are working, use this switch
4624                 {
4625                     // this branch is not preferred,
4626                     // because the manual said that integer mod and div operations are slow on gpu
4627                     pos_d = (ii % dims_a[d]);
4628                     ii = (ii / dims_a[d]);
4629                 }
4630                 else
4631                 {
4632                     pos_d = (ii & ((1 << log2_dims_a[d])-1)); //take the lower log2_dims bits
4633                     ii = (ii >> log2_dims_a[d]);  //shift those lower log2_dims bits off of ii
4634                 }
4635                 a_data_i += pos_d * a_str[d];
4636                 z_data_i += pos_d * z_str[d];
4637             }
4638         }
4639         // now we've got pointers a_data_i and z_data_i into element 0 of the slice over which we are reducing
4640         // do a similar loop
4641 
4642         float sum = 0.0f;
4643         switch(n_reduce_dims)
4644         {
4645             case 0:
4646                 {
4647                     sum = a_data_i[0];
4648                 }
4649                 break;
4650             case 1:
4651                 {
4652                     const int stride = a_str[reduce_dim0];
4653                     const float * a_data_i_max = a_data_i + dims_a[reduce_dim0] * stride;
4654                     while (a_data_i != a_data_i_max)
4655                     {
4656                         sum += a_data_i[0];
4657                         a_data_i += stride;
4658                     }
4659                 }
4660                 break;
4661             case 2:
4662                 {
4663                     int rd = reduce_dim0+1;
4664                     for (; rd < nd; ++rd)
4665                     {
4666                         if (a_str[rd] && (!z_str[rd])) // this means 'rd' is a dimension we are reducing over
4667                             break;
4668                     }
4669                     const int stride0 = a_str[reduce_dim0];
4670                     const int stride1 = a_str[rd];
4671                     for (int ii = 0; ii < dims_a[rd]; ++ii)
4672                     {
4673                         const float * a_data_ri = a_data_i + ii * stride1;
4674                         const float * a_data_ri_max = a_data_ri + dims_a[reduce_dim0] * stride0;
4675                         while (a_data_ri != a_data_ri_max)
4676                         {
4677                             sum += a_data_ri[0];
4678                             a_data_ri += stride0;
4679                         }
4680                     }
4681                 };
4682                 break;
4683             default:
4684                 {
4685                     for (unsigned int reduce_i = 0; reduce_i < n_reduce_elements; ++reduce_i)
4686                     {
4687                         //TODO: optimize this loop to work more like theano's Elemwise.  It's serial code.
4688                         unsigned int reduce_ii = reduce_i;
4689                         const float * a_data_ri = a_data_i;
4690 
4691                         //This loop finds the element in the a slice to add.
4692                         for (unsigned int rd = reduce_dim0; rd < nd; ++rd)
4693                         {
4694                             unsigned int pos_d;
4695                             if (a_str[rd] && (!z_str[rd])) // this means 'd' is a dimension we are reducing over
4696                             {
4697                                 if (log2_dims_a[rd]==-1)
4698                                 {
4699                                     // this branch is not preferred,
4700                                     // because the manual said that integer mod and div operations are slow on gpu
4701                                     pos_d = (reduce_ii % dims_a[rd]);
4702                                     reduce_ii = (reduce_ii / dims_a[rd]);
4703                                 }
4704                                 else
4705                                 {
4706                                     pos_d = (reduce_ii & ((1 << log2_dims_a[rd])-1)); //take the lower log2_dims bits
4707                                     reduce_ii = (reduce_ii >> log2_dims_a[rd]);  //shift those lower log2_dims bits off of ii
4708                                 }
4709                                 a_data_ri += pos_d * a_str[rd];
4710                             }
4711                         }
4712                         sum += a_data_ri[0];
4713                     }
4714                 }
4715         }
4716         z_data_i[0] = sum;
4717     }
4718 }
4719 
4720 static __global__ void kernel_reduce_sum_1011(
4721         const unsigned int d0,
4722         const unsigned int d1,
4723         const unsigned int d2,
4724         const unsigned int d3,
4725         const float *A, const int sA0, const int sA1, const int sA2, const int sA3,
4726         float * Z, const int sZ0)
4727 {
4728     const int threadCount = blockDim.x * blockDim.y * blockDim.z;
4729     const int threadNum = threadIdx.z * blockDim.x * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
4730     extern __shared__ float buf[];
4731     float mysum = 0.0f;
4732 
4733     if (warpSize != 32)
4734     {
4735         return;  //TODO: set error code
4736     }
4737 
4738     for (int i0 = threadIdx.z; i0 < d0; i0 += blockDim.z)
4739     {
4740         float Ai = A[i0 * sA0 + blockIdx.x * sA1 + threadIdx.y * sA2 + threadIdx.x * sA3];
4741         mysum += Ai;
4742     }
4743     buf[threadNum] = mysum;
4744     __syncthreads();
4745 
4746     // rest of function is handled by one warp
4747     if (threadNum < warpSize)
4748     {
4749         for (int i = threadNum + warpSize; i < threadCount; i += warpSize)
4750         {
4751             mysum += buf[i];
4752         }
4753         buf[threadNum] = mysum;
4754         if (threadNum < 16)
4755         {
4756             //reduce so that threadNum 0 has the sum of everything
4757             if(threadNum + 16 < threadCount) buf[threadNum] += buf[threadNum+16];
4758             if(threadNum + 8 < threadCount) buf[threadNum] += buf[threadNum+8];
4759             if(threadNum + 4 < threadCount) buf[threadNum] += buf[threadNum+4];
4760             if(threadNum + 2 < threadCount) buf[threadNum] += buf[threadNum+2];
4761             if(threadNum + 1 < threadCount) buf[threadNum] += buf[threadNum+1];
4762             if (threadNum == 0)
4763             {
4764                 Z[blockIdx.x*sZ0] = buf[0];
4765             }
4766         }
4767     }
4768 }
4769 /**
4770  * Dimensions in which the self has size 1 and A has size > 1 are considered summing dimensions
4771  * Dimensions in which self has size > 1 and A has size > 1 are considered non-summing dimensions, and in this case their sizes must be equal.
4772  */
4773 int
4774 CudaNdarray_reduce_sum(CudaNdarray * self, CudaNdarray * A)
4775 {
4776     int verbose = 0;
4777     //check input rank
4778     if (self->nd != A->nd)
4779     {
4780         PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "Rank mismatch in CudaNdarray_sum: %i vs %i", self->nd, A->nd);
4781         return -1;
4782     }
4783     for (int i = 0; i < self->nd; ++i)
4784     {
4785         if ((CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i] > 1) && (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i] != CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[i]))
4786         {
4787             PyErr_Format(PyExc_TypeError, "Dimension mismatch in CudaNdarray_sum: self->dim[%i] == %i , A->dim[%i] = %i",
4788                     i, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i], i, CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[i]);
4789             return -1;
4790         }
4791     }
4792 
4793     int n_summations = (unsigned int)CudaNdarray_SIZE(self);
4794     if (verbose)
4795     {
4796         std::cerr << "reduce_sum n_summations " << n_summations  << '\n';
4797         std::cerr << "reduce_sum nd " << self->nd  << '\n';
4798         fprint_CudaNdarray(stderr, A);
4799         fprint_CudaNdarray(stderr, self);
4800     }
4801     if (0 && (A->nd == 4) //check to see if kernel_reduce_sum_1011 applies
4802             && (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[0] == 1)
4803             && (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[2] == 1)
4804             && (CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[3] == 1)
4805        )
4806     {
4807         dim3 n_threads(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[3], CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[2]);
4808         dim3 n_blocks(CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1]);
4809         while (n_threads.x * n_threads.y * n_threads.z < NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK) ++n_threads.z;
4810         n_threads.z -= 1;
4811         if (n_threads.z > 64) n_threads.z = 64;
4812         if (n_threads.z)
4813         {
4814             if (verbose) printf("trying kernel_reduce_sum_1011\n");
4815             int n_shared = sizeof(float) * n_threads.x * n_threads.y * n_threads.z;
4816             kernel_reduce_sum_1011<<<n_blocks, n_threads, n_shared>>>(
4817                     CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[0],
4818                     CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[1],
4819                     CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[2],
4820                     CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(A)[3],
4821                     CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(A),
4822                     CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[0],
4823                     CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[1],
4824                     CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[2],
4825                     CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(A)[3],
4826                     CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self),
4827                     CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[1]);
4828             CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
4829             if (cudaSuccess == cudaGetLastError()) return 0;
4830             if (verbose) printf("failed, falling back to kernel_reduce_sum\n");
4831         }
4832     }
4833 
4834     int n_threads_per_block = std::min(n_summations,
4835             NUM_VECTOR_OP_THREADS_PER_BLOCK);
4836     int n_blocks = std::min(ceil_intdiv(n_summations,n_threads_per_block),
4837             NUM_VECTOR_OP_BLOCKS);
4838     int n_structure_cache = self->nd * 4 * sizeof(int);
4839 
4840     if (verbose)
4841     {
4842         std::cerr << "n_blocks, n_threads_per_block " << n_blocks << ' ' << n_threads_per_block  << '\n';
4843     }
4844     assert (self->nd > 0);
4845     assert (self->nd == A->nd);
4846     kernel_reduce_sum<<<n_blocks, n_threads_per_block, n_structure_cache>>>(
4847             n_summations,
4848             self->nd,
4849             CudaNdarray_DEV_DIMS(A),
4850             CudaNdarray_DEV_LOG2DIMS(A),
4851             CudaNdarray_DEV_STRIDES(A),
4852             CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(A),
4853             CudaNdarray_DEV_STRIDES(self),
4854             CudaNdarray_DEV_DATA(self));
4855     CNDA_THREAD_SYNC;
4856     cudaError_t err = cudaGetLastError();
4857     if (cudaSuccess != err)
4858     {
4859         PyErr_Format(PyExc_RuntimeError, "Cuda error: %s: %s.\n", "kernel_reduce_sum", cudaGetErrorString(err));
4860         return -1;
4861     }
4862     return 0;
4863 }

4884 /**
4885  *
4886  *  pattern is a permutation of [0, 1, ... self->nd-1] with the following twists:
4887  *  - an element 'd' of the permutation can be dropped if CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[d] == 1
4888  *  - any number of '-1' elements can be in the pattern, and they will cause new ranks (with dim==1) to be inserted.
4889  *
4890  *  For example, if CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self) == [4, 5, 1, 6], and pattern = [0,3,-1,-1, 1], then CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self) would be modified to become:
4891  *     [4, 6, 1, 1, 5] (we dropped the original dim[2]==1, and inserted two singleton dimensions with the -1s.
4892  */
4893 int
4894 CudaNdarray_dimshuffle(CudaNdarray * self, unsigned int len, const int * pattern)
4895 {
4896     //TODO: pass a workspace pointer to avoid the internal malloc
4897     int * newdims = (int *)malloc(sizeof(int) * (len + len + self->nd)); //we tack on the taken buffer here for speed of not having to malloc twice.
4898     int * newstrides = newdims + len;
4899     int * dims_taken = newstrides + len;
4900     if (!newdims)
4901     {
4902         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_MemoryError, "CudaNdarray_dimshuffle: Failed to allocate temporary space");
4903         return -1;
4904     }
4905     for (int i = 0; i < self->nd; ++i)
4906     {
4907         dims_taken[i] = 0;
4908     }
4909     for (int i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4910     {
4911         if (pattern[i] < 0)
4912         {
4913             newdims[i] = 1;
4914             newstrides[i] = 0;
4915         }
4916         else if(dims_taken[pattern[i]])
4917         {
4918             PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "Cudandarray_dimshuffle: invalid pattern for Cudandarray_dimshuffle. You used the dimensions %d multiple time",
4919                          pattern[i]);
4920             free(newdims);
4921             return -1;
4922         }
4923         else if (pattern[i]>= self->nd)
4924         {
4925             PyErr_Format(PyExc_ValueError, "Cudandarray_dimshuffle: invalid pattern for Cudandarray_dimshuffle. You asked for a dimensions that don't exist %d for a %d dims CudaNdarray",
4926                          pattern[i], self->nd);
4927             free(newdims);
4928             return -1;
4929         }
4930         else
4931         {
4932             newdims[i] = CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[pattern[i]];
4933             newstrides[i] = CudaNdarray_HOST_STRIDES(self)[pattern[i]];
4934             dims_taken[pattern[i]] = 1;
4935         }
4936     }
4937     //Check if we dropped not broadcastable dims
4938     for (int i = 0; i < self->nd; ++i)
4939     {
4940         if (dims_taken[i]==0 && CudaNdarray_HOST_DIMS(self)[i]!=1)
4941         {
4942             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "Cudandarray_dimshuffle: You cannot drop a non-broadcastable dimension.");
4943             free(newdims);
4944             return -1;
4945         }
4946     }
4947     //swap this structure in for the one in self, and sync to the card
4948     if (CudaNdarray_set_nd(self, len))
4949     {
4950         free(newdims);
4951         return -1;
4952     }
4953     for (int i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4954     {
4955         CudaNdarray_set_dim(self, i, newdims[i]);
4956         CudaNdarray_set_stride(self, i, newstrides[i]);
4957     }
4958     if (cnda_copy_structure_to_device(self))
4959     {
4960         free(newdims);
4961         return -1;
4962     }
4963     free(newdims);
4964     return 0;
4965 }

4969 /**
4970  *
4971  *  This is the function that bind to python.
4972  *  See CudaNdarray_dimshuffle to call from C.
4973  *  We use -1 to mean 'x' as in Tensor Dimshuffle.
4974  */
4975 PyObject *
4976 CudaNdarray_Dimshuffle(PyObject* _unused, PyObject* args)
4977 {
4978     PyObject * self = NULL;
4979     PyObject * pattern_object = NULL;
4980     int * pattern = NULL;

4982     int success = -1;
4983     //const int * dims = NULL;
4984 
4985     //args should consist of two python objects ("OO")
4986     if (! PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "OO", &self, &pattern_object))
4987         return NULL;
4988 
4989     if (!CudaNdarray_Check(self) )
4990     {
4991         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "First argument to cuda_ndarray.dimshuffle must be a CudaNdarray");
4992         return NULL;
4993     }
4994 
4995     //parse pattern_object into int * pattern
4996 
4997     Py_ssize_t pattern_dim =  PyObject_Length(pattern_object);
4998 
4999     if (pattern_dim < 0)
5000     {
5001         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "Couldn't get length of third argument to cuda_ndarray.dimshuffle");
5002         return NULL;
5003     }
5004 
5005     pattern = (int *) alloca( pattern_dim * sizeof(int));
5006 
5007     for (Py_ssize_t i = 0; i < pattern_dim; i++)
5008     {
5009         PyObject * idx = PyLong_FromLong(i);
5010 
5011         if (idx == NULL)
5012         {
5013             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_Exception, "Couldn't make long object to loop over list/tuple");
5014             goto CudaNdarray_dimshuffle_fail;
5015         }

5019         PyObject * elem = PyObject_GetItem(pattern_object, idx);
5020 
5021         if (elem == NULL)

5024             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "Third argument to dimshuffle must be list or tuple of integers");
5025             goto CudaNdarray_dimshuffle_fail;
5026         }
5027 
5028         elem_value = PyInt_AsLong(elem);
5029 
5030         if (elem_value == -1 && PyErr_Occurred() )
5031         {
5032             Py_XDECREF(elem);
5033             PyErr_SetString(PyExc_ValueError, "Third argument to dimshuffle must be list or tuple of integers");
5034             goto CudaNdarray_dimshuffle_fail;
5035         }
5036

5038 
5039         Py_XDECREF( elem );
5040         Py_XDECREF( idx );
5041     }
5042 
5043     //allocate rval
5044     rval =  (PyObject *) CudaNdarray_View((CudaNdarray *) self);
5045 
5046     if (rval == NULL)
5047     {
5048         //CudaNdarray_New should have set the exception string
5049         goto CudaNdarray_dimshuffle_fail;
5050     }
5051

5059 
5060     if (success != 0)
5061     {
5062         //Exception string should already be set by CudaNdarray_dimshuffle
5063         goto CudaNdarray_dimshuffle_fail;
5064     }

5101 int
5102 CudaNdarray_EqualAndIgnore(CudaNdarray *cnda1, CudaNdarray *cnda2, int ignoreSync, int ignoreBase)
5103 {
5104     int verbose = 0;
5105 
5106     if (!ignoreSync && cnda1->dev_structure_fresh != cnda2->dev_structure_fresh)
5107     {
5108         if(verbose) fprintf(stdout, "CUDANDARRAY_EQUAL FAILED : 1\n");
5109         return 0;
5110     }
5111 
5112     if (cnda1->nd != cnda2->nd)
5113     {
5114         if(verbose) fprintf(stdout, "CUDANDARRAY_EQUAL FAILED : 2\n");
5115         return 0;
5116     }
5117 
5118     for (int i=0; i < 2*cnda1->nd; i++)
5119     {
5120         if (cnda1->host_structure[i] != cnda2->host_structure[i])
5121         {
5122             if(verbose)
5123                 fprintf(stdout, "CUDANDARRAY_EQUAL : host_structure : %d, %d, %d\n", i, cnda1->host_structure[i], cnda2->host_structure[i]);
5124             return 0;
5125         }
5126     }
5127 
5128     if (!ignoreBase && cnda1->base != cnda2->base)
5129     {
5130         if(verbose) fprintf(stdout, "CUDANDARRAY_EQUAL FAILED : 4");
5131         return 0;
5132     }
5133     else if (cnda1->data_allocated != cnda2->data_allocated)
5134     {
5135         if(verbose) fprintf(stdout, "CUDANDARRAY_EQUAL FAILED : 5");
5136         return 0;
5137     }
5138     else if (cnda1->data_allocated && cnda1->devdata != cnda2->devdata)
5139     {
5140         if(verbose) fprintf(stdout, "CUDANDARRAY_EQUAL FAILED : 6");
5141         // no need to check devdata if data is not allocated
5142         return 0;
5143     }
5144 
5145     return 1;
5146 }

5155 int
5156 cnda_copy_structure_to_device(const CudaNdarray * self)
5157 {
5158     //If the device structure do not exists, create it.
5159     //We allocate it here as we do not need it often.
5160     //In fact, we need it so infrequently that we expect
5161     //that most object won't need it. Not allocating it
5162     //save a significant when creating object.
5163     //This speed up a benchmark by 8% with the gc.
5164     if (!self->dev_structure)
5165     {
5166         int struct_size = cnda_structure_size(self->nd);
5167         if (struct_size)
5168         {
5169             self->dev_structure = (int*)device_malloc(struct_size* sizeof(int));
5170             if (NULL == self->dev_structure)
5171             {
5172                 return -1;
5173             }
5174         }
5175     }
5176     if (cublasSetVector(cnda_structure_size(self->nd),
5177                         sizeof(int),
5178                         self->host_structure,
5179                         1,
5180                         self->dev_structure,
5181                         1) != CUBLAS_STATUS_SUCCESS)
5182     {
5183         PyErr_SetString(PyExc_RuntimeError, "error copying structure to device memory");
5184         return -1;
5185     }
5186     self->dev_structure_fresh = 1;
5187     return 0;
5188 }

5196             return NULL;
5197     }

def colour_for_z_samples(samples):
    mean = samples.mean(axis=0)
    mean1 = mean[dim1]
    mean2 = mean[dim2]
    colour = np.zeros_like(samples[:, 0])
    colour[np.logical_and(samples[:, dim1] < mean1,  samples[:, dim2] < mean2)] = 0
    colour[np.logical_and(samples[:, dim1] < mean1,  samples[:, dim2] >= mean2)] = 1
    colour[np.logical_and(samples[:, dim1] >= mean1, samples[:, dim2] < mean2)] = 2
    colour[np.logical_and(samples[:, dim1] >= mean1, samples[:, dim2] >= mean2)] = 3
    colour[((samples[:, dim1] - mean1) ** 2 + (samples[:, dim2] - mean2) ** 2) < 1e-4] = 6
    return colour
